When we tried to enter an order to use up that grant there were no delivery times available before May 27, because of the holiday weekend. We spoke with Charity in Partner Support and she told us to submit our order with a May 28 delivery day and then email you to get the deadline extended by a day.

In addition to extending the deadline, please have your finance department deduct the order from the above mentioned grant. The computer automatically deducted it from our next MOCO grant which expires in June.
I apologize for causing you extra work. Thank you for your assistance. Don't hesitate to call if you have any questions.

Status of delivery of Groceries to go order ,PART1-8571,82345,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,.tnsuns.oeecem-tmeti@ivstsay,snv.yi@taceomttunssseee-t.mi,2025-02-14 02:30:00,2025-02-20 01:30:00,,2025-02-14 02:47:00,,"Hello - We have not received our Grocery to Go Order as of 2:30 pm. It was supposed to be delivered by 2:00 pm. Please advise. If it is not coming a robo call needs to go out so all the seniors do not show up.

We hope this message finds you well. Today, February 12th 2025, the Capital Area Food Bank is operating solely in an administrative capacity, and there will be no deliveries or pickups due to the current weather conditions.

For partners who have orders scheduled for tomorrow or Friday, we plan to operate under normal conditions. However, if you anticipate that your agency will be closed due to the weather, please reach out to Customer Relations as soon as possible to discuss rescheduling your order at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org or 202-644-9845.

Additionally, even if your site remains open, we require confirmation that your location has been safely plowed and salted to allow for safe deliveries. If a driver arrives at your site and finds it is not adequately prepared, please be aware that your agency may incur a restocking fee. Our delivery equipment cannot navigate through snow or ice safely, and we prioritize the safety of both our drivers and your staff.

We appreciate your cooperation and understanding as we work together to ensure everyone's safety during this weather event. We are actively monitoring the situation and will keep you updated with any changes regarding our operations for the rest of the week.
Thank you for your partnership. Stay safe and warm!

Customer Relations  {quote}",1. h3. {color:#5a5a5a}I saw the post in the newletter and on the site.{color}
When can we place an order for 6/7 deliveries? The next day is a scheduled distribution day for us.
Seeking to reserve a delivery slot for 6/7.

On June 7th, the Capital Area Food Bank will be closing early. Only the 8am-10am delivery and 8am, 9am, and 10am pickup slots will be available. This will also affect the puller's schedule on Monday, June 10th, resulting in limited delivery and pickup windows. column2: {color:#172B4D}Weâ€™re happy to let you know that weâ€™ve received your order. \\  \\ To review the details of your order, including the delivery/pickup date, items ordered, price breakdown, and delivery/pickup time window, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History section inside the Account Overview.{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions, call us at 202-644-9845 or email {color}[{color:#172B4D} partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

{color:#172B4D}Returns: Upon receipt of your order, please ensure that you thoroughly review your order and contact us to report any missing or damaged items immediately. Per our SMART Shopping Training and Agency Agreement, signing for your order upon receipt is confirmation that you have received all products ordered. To review our Return Policy and learn what Capital Area Food Bank considers valid and nonvalid return scenarios, please visit PartnerLink and scroll down to the bottom of the screen for a copy.  \\  \\ You will receive an email reminder 24 hours before your order locks in our system. Please remember that your order will close for edits and changes three business days before your delivery/pickup date. If you are having difficulty editing or changing the details of your order, please let us know. \\  *Important for Deliveries:* If the shipping address on your sales order is incorrect, please get in touch with your Regional Coordinator, who will happily assist with ensuring your delivery reaches the correct address on your order date. \\  \\ Thank you,  \\  \\ The Partner Support Team{color}

{color:#172B4D} Thank you for reaching out to us! Please reschedule the delivery for ACTS Hunger Prevention Center. If it helps, the sales order number is SO190198.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Please note that we are closed on Fridays.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Thank you again and take care,{color}
[CAUTION: This email originated from outside of the organization. Do not click links or open attachments unless you recognize the sender and know the content is safe]

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th.

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

M. B. C.,,,,,,,General Questions,English,,0.0,,Portal,10020,,service-request,Done,2023-06-13 02:15:00,00:04:57,"{""comment1"": ""06/13/2023 11:04;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Zelda, 

I hope you are doing well. One of a few things could be happening. 

1.) If you are in editing mode, which means you clicked â€œEdit Orderâ€ and you are viewing your card- there will be error messages saying that there are zero availability because there is no more left of that item to add to your order. Whatever you had on your order before starting to edit the order is secured but the error message is saying that there is no more of this item available to add more of. 

2.) If you did not hit save, which I see that you said you did- then you could have lost of the items. Previously, the old system held in the carts for 24 hours, but that is no longer the case. 

3.) The last instance is that throughout the day, our warehouse team members are continuously doing quality checks. If for any reason produce fails that quality check or the warehouse team deems it as not being able to â€˜make itâ€™ (quality wise) to the date it's supposed to be delivered it can be taken off of your order. 

I am looking at your order and I do see eggplant, potatoes, cucumbers and squash on your orders.

 Sent on August 19, 2024 8:04:20 AM EDT  {quote}"", ""comment6"": ""08/19/2024 02:44;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for your question. Once you complete the checkout process, your items are put on a sales order and finalized. The emails you receive are due to potential errors in our inventory or the pulling process that may cause changes to your order before delivery.

This can happen for two main reasons. Firstly, if the pulling team finds that the item's quality is not up to our standards for delivery, it may be removed from your order or the quantity decreased. This can occur when partners place orders well in advance and by the time the order is picked, the item may no longer meet our quality standards.

Secondly, if we run out of a certain product, this could be due to periodic inventory errors where the actual count of items doesn't match what's on the menu.

While we strive to minimize these occurrences, we send email notifications to keep partners informed in case such changes are necessary before their order is fulfilled.

Thank you,

Thank you for your question. Once you complete the checkout process, your items are put on a sales order and finalized. The emails you receive are due to potential errors in our inventory or the pulling process that may cause changes to your order before delivery. 

This can happen for two main reasons. Firstly, if the pulling team finds that the item's quality is not up to our standards for delivery, it may be removed from your order or the quantity decreased. This can occur when partners place orders well in advance and by the time the order is picked, the item may no longer meet our quality standards. 

Secondly, if we run out of a certain product, this could be due to periodic inventory errors where the actual count of items doesn't match what's on the menu. 

While we strive to minimize these occurrences, we send email notifications to keep partners informed in case such changes are necessary before their order is fulfilled. 

Thank you,

column1: Inquiry for SO189116 ,PART1-8146,78663,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,oaTdrllA goloy,raoAyolodllT g,2025-01-03 10:45:00,2025-01-09 01:30:00,,2025-01-03 12:44:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Dear Partner Support Team,{color}
{color:#172B4D} I hope this email finds you well. My name is Taylor Allgood, and I am with The Market at American University which recently placed an order through the Capital Area Food Bank.{color}

{color:#172B4D} We recently learned that oatmeal is now available for free on your website, and we would greatly appreciate including some in our current order for  *Monday, January 6*, if it is still possible to make modifications. We understand that the 24-hour window to modify or cancel the order has passed as of 1/1/25. However, since it has only been one day beyond this period, I wanted to kindly ask if you might be able to add a few boxes of oatmeal to our order.{color}
{color:#172B4D} We completely understand if the timing makes this addition difficult, but we wanted to reach out in case it is feasible. In any case, we truly thank you for all your support.{color}

thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""01/03/2025 12:51;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to us! We have an inclement weather policy that can be found on PartnerLink. Typically, when inclement weather is forecasted, we urge our partners to contact us in advance, before the Capital Area Food Bank makes a decision about whether we will be open for the day. This way, we can help reschedule orders to a later date if possible.

Please note that the Capital Area Food Bank does not follow government decisions regarding weather closures and delays. Our Operations Department and leadership team make decisions about our operating hours based on weather and road conditions to ensure the safety of our drivers and partners.

The earliest time I can schedule your order is January 13th. Please let me know if you would like to reschedule your order, and I can take care of it on our end.

Thank you again for reaching out!

Best regards,  
""D"""", ""comment3"": ""01/05/2025 07:21;712020:2bb9273c-7be5-434d-ad6f-1d0fe73d99c7;Good evening,

Thank you for your response and for sharing the Capital Area Food Bankâ€™s inclement weather policy.

I wanted to let you know that, as of 7:11 pm today, American University has officially closed for tomorrow, January 6, due to inclement weather. As a result, we will need to reschedule our order.

The proposed date of Monday, January 13 (between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM if possible) works well for me if it aligns with your schedule. Please let me know if this time works on your end or if another adjustment is needed.

Thank you for your understanding and flexibility. I look forward to hearing from you."", ""comment4"": ""01/05/2025 07:25;712020:2bb9273c-7be5-434d-ad6f-1d0fe73d99c7;Hello, I am sorry for the last-minute follow up. I just realized that on Monday, January 13, I am scheduled to attend CAFBâ€™s SNAP Enrollment Training from 11-1 pm. Seeing as though I will need to be present for the CAFB delivery, please let me know what other days and times next week may be available for delivery. If you have any openings on *Wednesday, January 15*, please let me know. Thank you!"", ""comment5"": ""01/07/2025 11:09;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning, 

I want to confirm that you spoke with a member of my team today. Your order has been rescheduled for tomorrow, depending on whether we are open. If there are any changes, we will keep you informed. 

Have a great day!""}",,0.0

column1: We would like to inform you that the Capital Area Food Bank will be closed on Tuesday, January 7th, 2025, due to inclement weather. On this day, there will be no pickups or deliveries, and any scheduled orders will be rescheduled once we reopen.

Please note that Customer Relations will also be closed on that day. All tickets and phone calls will be addressed upon our reopening when we will process rescheduling and cancellations. We will provide an update regarding our status for Wednesday later on Tuesday.

[^SalesOrd_8531916.pdf] _(46 kB)_"", ""comment2"": ""01/28/2025 12:09;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out about the expiration dates on your product. Unfortunately, we cannot provide specific expiration dates for these items. When a product is labeled as ""assorted,"" it means it is a compilation of dozens of different products under that category that have been donated. These items are sorted by our volunteer teams or donated in bulk. 

While our volunteers are instructed not to include expired foods, items that are past their ""best by"" or ""sell by"" dates are considered acceptable for consumption and may still be included. We encourage all partners receiving these donated cases to be aware of this and to use the Food Coding Guide created by our Food Resources team and Nutrition Department. Additionally, we recommend using your knowledge of food safety and your senses (sight, smell, and texture) to determine if the food is in good condition.

I apologize for not being able to provide further guidance on this matter. The nature of donated products, especially assorted bins, makes it difficult to pinpoint a specific expiration date for a mix of different items.

[^Food Coding Guidance.pdf]

Thank you,  
""D""""}",,0.0

Good afternoon,

Thank you for submitting this ticket to Customer Service. I have reviewed your reported issues and consulted with my colleagues in our Food Resources and Operations Teams.

Regarding the tortillas, I apologize that they were sent out after their expiration date. I have reported this to the Food Resources Team for further investigation. However, since you received them, I have processed a credit of $45.60 for the tortillas you ordered (which had a discount applied). This credit will be applied to the invoice associated with your order, Invoice #180569.

As for the flavored water, the date on the items indicated ""BB,"" which stands for ""best by."" Many of our donated foods may be past their best by or sell by dates. These dates are intended to inform you of when the item is not at its peak quality, not about food safety. The items are still safe to consume, and we encourage our partners to use their judgment. If there are any signs of concernâ€”such as changes in taste, smell, or packagingâ€”do not distribute the item and please let us know.

[^Food Coding Guidance.pdf]

Thank you,

column1: Drivers are not able to see the special notes that are entered when order is placed ,PART1-7899,74077,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,mrivtaahelyoea@.mo7ch100,7cv1laheytmho.0amaie@0ro,2024-11-20 07:59:00,2024-11-27 01:30:00,,2024-11-21 02:25:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hello,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Of late, I am not getting a phone call letting me know that the driver is on their way to our Pantry. I enter a note for each of our orders asking that a driver call as they are leaving the warehouse so that our volunteers have enough time to get to our location when the truck arrives.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} We are a small organization - and our Pantry is just that - a large closet that stores a tremendous amount of food. We deliver our food to the clients so there is no 'office' available for volunteers to wait.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} When I scheduled today's delivery, a morning slot was not available. I had written asking if there would be any way to move our delivery up since we are normally an early delivery partner. I was told that the delivery schedule was full for the morning so that I had to keep my noon - 2 pm slot.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I happened to be at the Pantry to do some stocking and the truck arrived at 10 AM!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Luckily we were able to meet the driver with no delay to his schedule.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I would appreciate it if drivers could please view the special notes/instructions for each delivery. I have been told by a few drivers that they do not see the special notes on their delivery receipt.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Pantry Manager, Bethesda Help{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}",B. H.,Ops Issue,,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Feedback - Concern / Negative -> Operations,Email Request,English,Feedback Communicated,0.0,,Email to Jira,10800,10:34:00,service-request,Done,2024-11-21 02:25:00,00:05:08.600000,"{""comment1"": ""11/21/2024 12:05;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon, Angela,

  I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for your valuable feedback regarding our delivery process.  I will connect with our Transportation Team to clarify the issue and explore ways to improve it. Each morning, our Transportation Leadership prints out the day's sales orders, which should include the notes you and your team leave. I will double-check to ensure this process is still in place, as we established a notes section specifically for partners to provide important information for our drivers.  Additionally, I want to mention that there are times when drivers may finish their deliveries earlier than expected, or we may have more drivers available than anticipated. In such cases, drivers are instructed to call you to ask if you would like to receive your order before your scheduled delivery window. If you decline, they should wait until your designated delivery window.  I will reach out to confirm these details and will follow up with you. I understand that the current situation is not ideal and the implications it has on your distribution. 

Best regards,  

 ""D"""", ""comment2"": ""11/21/2024 02:24;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon, Angela, 

I just spoke with Joe, the Transportation Manager. He informed me that he discussed the delivery process and the expectation for courtesy calls with the driver who made your delivery yesterday, as well as the team of drivers during their morning meeting today. 

Joe confirmed that drivers should be able to see the notes you leave on your sales orders. More importantly, it is mandatory for them to call all partners before their deliveries, even if they are within the designated delivery window. This call is to inform you that they are on their way. In instances where drivers can make earlier deliveries, they must consult with you first to see if you can accommodate the earlier arrival; if not, they are expected to wait until the agreed delivery window.

If you continue to experience issues regarding this matter, please let me know, and I will arrange for Joe to give you a call to discuss it further.

Best,  
""D""""}",,0.0
{color:#172B4D} Our order (SO187548) arrived on Wednesday at 10:30 am. The order was scheduled to arrive between 12 - 2 pm. I did not receive a call.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Of late, I have not been receiving calls from the driver letting me know that they have left the warehouse.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Our Pantry is VERY small (but mighty). My volunteers that help unload the pallets do not arrive until I let them know the truck's ETA. So if a driver doesn't call, I may not be at the Pantry to receive it.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Will is a great driver - so I did not say anything about not giving me a call on Wednesday - I happen to be at the Pantry so he was able to drop off my 2 pallets earlier than scheduled.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} My next order (1/8/2025) is again scheduled for a 12 - 2 pm delivery... though I would rather have a morning delivery appointment. Can my order please be moved?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Pantry Manager, Bethesda Help{color}",B. Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders ,PART1-8181,78744,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,.syemt.ie-sseisteoctt@nvmanu,myastsnetc.iteso-.env@smitue,2025-01-07 12:43:00,2025-01-12 01:30:00,,2025-01-08 01:29:00,2025-01-08 12:00:00,"{color:#172B4D}Hello -{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} We would very much like to reschedule our Wednesday 1/8 delivery as soon as possible. Like many other of your partners, we rely almost exclusively on the food from CAFB. Our client demand is at its highest during the first 10 days of the month - so tomorrow's scheduled delivery is critical for our operations.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Please let me know when our delivery can be rescheduled.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Thank you for your continued support - and great work -{color}

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th.

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

Customer Relations",B. Thank you!

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

column1: Fw: BPSOS - Delivery Issue ,PART1-7852,73714,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,gnl iAannKa,Ain lanngaK,2024-11-15 02:19:00,2024-11-23 01:30:00,,2024-11-19 12:24:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hi Team,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I hope you all are doing well. It seems some feedback from partners around the pallets being too high or double stacked have really increased in the past couple of weeks. I wanted to touch base with you all to see what may be causing this and if there are any possible solutions we can come up with to help partners while not impeding your processes!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} This is Than from BPSOS. I am writing this to let you know about an issue with our food delivery this morning 11/15.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} We ordered a total of 8 or 9 pallets of vegetables this morning. However, those pallets were stacked on top of each other as a pair when they were delivered. We asked the driver if he could bring the pallets down since they are very heavy (about 800 lbs each) and our office did not have any equipment to handle that. He said that there was nothing he could do because they were loaded into the truck like that.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} We did have this issue in the past and it took our staff (which comprised of many seniors) a tremendous amount of effort to handle it. We always appreciate CAFB for providing the food for free, but in the future, it would be great if you do not stack pallets on top of each other. If you have no choice but to do so, please let us know in advance.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:blue} If a federal employee or in the military, you can support our mission through CFC Charity No: 10038{color}{color:blue}{color}

column1: Fw: BPSOS - Food Order Issue ,PART1-7923,74411,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,lna KiAanng,AingKnla na,2024-11-25 10:40:00,2024-11-29 01:31:00,,2024-11-25 02:21:00,,"----

{color:#172B4D} Happy Monday! This is Than from BPSOS. I am writing this because we encountered a technical issue on the website. Last Friday 11/22, we tried to add a few items, namely 2 of the  *800908 Cabbage, Green Local 675# BIN 1/675 lbs Bin* into our cart, to be delivered this Wednesday 11/27. However, it said that those items were not available on that selected date, but in the item description, it said that it will still be available until 12/10. As a result, we could not select those items back then. It was pretty late then, so I was not able to email you until today.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I know that we may past the deadline for edit order; however, is it possible for you to remove all of the ""300597 Turkey Breast, 6-9# Basted w/ Gravy Packet 1/30.42486 lbs Case"" from our cart, and replace them with 2 of the ""800908 Cabbage, Green Local 675# BIN 1/675 lbs Bin?"" Additionally, do we still need to order more than 1000 lbs to be eligible for delivery?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I know that we are asking a lot Alanna, but we want to make sure that our vulnerable and underserved population can enjoy a good Thanksgiving this week. We would appreciate a lot if you can help us.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

column2: {color:#172B4D}Weâ€™re happy to let you know that weâ€™ve received your order. \\  \\To review the details of your order, including the delivery/pickup date, items ordered, price breakdown, and delivery/pickup time window, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History section inside the Account Overview.{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions, call us at 202-644-9845 or email {color}[{color:#172B4D}partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

{color:#172B4D}Returns: Upon receipt of your order, please ensure that you thoroughly review your order and contact us to report any missing or damaged items immediately. Per our SMART Shopping Training and Agency Agreement, signing for your order upon receipt is confirmation that you have received all products ordered. To review our Return Policy and learn what Capital Area Food Bank considers valid and nonvalid return scenarios, please visit PartnerLink and scroll down to the bottom of the screen for a copy.  \\  \\You will receive an email reminder 24 hours before your order locks in our system. Please remember that your order will close for edits and changes three business days before your delivery/pickup date. If you are having difficulty editing or changing the details of your order, please let us know. \\  *Important for Deliveries:* If the shipping address on your sales order is incorrect, please get in touch with your Regional Coordinator, who will happily assist with ensuring your delivery reaches the correct address on your order date. \\  \\Thank you,  \\  \\The Partner Support Team{color}

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours

column1: CCF Produce Hub Issue ,PART1-7904,74210,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,crrarF aareeG,rcFraeer raGa,2024-11-21 12:08:00,2024-11-29 01:31:00,,2024-11-25 02:40:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Good afternoon,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I wanted to follow up with you all regarding the issue with Capital Christian Fellowship's produce hub earlier this week. CCF adds food and edits the SO I make for their produce hubs. In the past few months, they have added thousands of pounds of food to these orders, making them close to 40k pounds sometimes. For the most recent hub order, someone at CCF accidentally removed 3k pounds of produce meant for the produce hub. Christ let me know that this can happen since the produce is marked as available for agencies and CAFB staff.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} We are having a meeting tomorrow with CCF to discuss the produce hub orders. I wanted to reach out to you all to get your insight on whether it would be beneficial for Transportation/Ops if I told CCF  that  *they cannot add/modify*  produce hub SOs anymore. However, I wouldn't want CCF to create additional orders during the same time and further strain the capacity of Transportation/Ops. If there is a specific pound limit that I should tell them not to exceed when adding food to the produce hub SOs, I can do that as well.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} I know that the produce limitations will impact their ordering, so their order sizes will probably decrease in the next few months. Please let me know if there is anything you would like me to mention during the meeting tomorrow. Thank you again for all your help!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

column5:
thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""11/25/2024 02:37;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon, Grace,  

I hope you are doing well. I wanted to bring this matter to Austin and discuss it with her. I understand the implications of the large orders and the concerns surrounding the removal of produce for the produce hub. When I spoke to Austin, she suggested that the first step should be to have a conversation with the partner to explain the implications of their edits to the order. They need to be mindful that they donâ€™t want to lose their produce items meant for the hub and that they should be aware of the weight of their orders when placing them.  

Here are two key points I discussed with Austin:  

1. Currently, we do not have a formal limit for orders, so we cannot tell them what a limit would be. Operations and ERP/IT are working on measures to ensure that for large orders, the number of delivery blocks corresponds appropriately. For example, two weeks ago, Capital Christianâ€™s order required five trucks for delivery but only occupied one slot, which is unrealistic. For now, we can only ensure that Operations is aware and prepared for these situations.

 2. Austin mentioned that if this situation continues to cause recurring issues and impacts the produce hub's participating sitesâ€”resulting in a loss of produceâ€”we can consider locking their orders for the produce hubs and requesting that they create a separate order. However, this could complicate matters since Operations has asked us to consolidate orders for the same partner to avoid having one sales order versus two. We can explore this locking option as a last resort if recurring issues continue. 

 I hope this clarifies the situation, and please let me know if you need any assistance in engaging with the partner. 

 Best,  

 ""D""""}",,0.0

Is it possible to carry over the items from SO176185 to our order for Tuesday, October 1 (SO177213) and the one from SO176188 to our order for Wednesday, October 2 (SO177245).
If this is possible, it would be so great!
I look forward to your response!

FW: Produce Hub Request ,PART1-7199,65996,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,cttd.hphigelncoarararm@asoiaii, krAeitauusFgc,2024-08-19 09:39:00,2024-08-29 01:32:00,,2024-08-21 03:42:00,,"Good morning,

Do you think the request not to stack could be adhered to? If so, I will put a note on their future produce hub orders. I am not sure who to loop in from ops, so please feel free to loop them in as needed.
I hope my email finds you well.

I have a request about the Produce Hub: is it possible that the pallets of produce are not stacked on top of each other? SEED comes with a truck like the one from CAFB so it uses the pallet jack to pick up their produce but when the pallets are stacked on top of each other, we have no way to lower the pallet of produce which is on top which we forced to cut the cardboard, to extract the product into a bin so that another partner can have its product. If the pallets come individually, each organization has the possibility of collecting its pallet of produce to its truck.
Also I looked at the order for the Hub but I only saw 50 squash boxes instead of 176 (the 58 boxes are the ones I ordered for my distribution). Will the rest be added later?

Capital Area Food Bank"", ""comment3"": ""08/19/2024 10:13;712020:38c82492-84fe-40dc-8901-61d65a68f6d3;Good morning Augusta I will let ""D"" know about this feedback and this could be addressed during the inventory meeting tomorrow. I will let you know if I receive any updates

CiArra"", ""comment4"": ""08/19/2024 02:07;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for submitting your request. I have forwarded this information to our Operations Teams so they can assist and provide a definitive answer on what can be done. Our Operations Team has specific reasons for the way pallets and trucks are packaged, in order to maximize truck space for loading your entire orders at once. I will update you as soon as I receive a response from the team.

Thank you,

""D"""", ""comment5"": ""08/19/2024 02:16;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:3e811295-a79f-43b5-9b94-8d895785c52a;My request is only in the case of produce for the Hub because it facilitates the sharing between the different partners.

Thank you in advance"", ""comment6"": ""08/21/2024 03:41;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you again for bringing up this question. I have spoken to our Operations Manager in the DC warehouse, and unfortunately, we are unable to unstack or repack the pallets of produce in a different manner due to the truck's space capacity and efficiency reasons. Packing the pallets differently would require sending multiple trucks, causing inefficiency, and we also do not have the bandwidth to unstack and unpackage the cases and pallets of produce for each partner participating in the produce hub. 

One suggestion is that your agency acquire a pallet jack during the next round of capacity grants to assist with this issue. I will also pass this feedback on to the Operations Leadership team for consideration, but currently, our Operations Team cannot accommodate it under our current operating procedures.

I apologize for this.

Thanks,

""D"""", ""comment7"": ""08/22/2024 09:23;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:3e811295-a79f-43b5-9b94-8d895785c52a;Thank you so much for your explanation\!

Be blessed!"", ""comment8"": ""08/22/2024 09:23;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.""}",,0.0

column1: REQUEST ABOUT THE PRODUCE ALLOCATION LIMIT ,PART1-7780,72959,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,ntrpcdm@aaiht.ehasirriooacliag,ittaedianorcrshhmcagpaaii.lr@o,2024-11-07 11:22:00,2024-11-13 01:30:00,,2024-11-07 11:29:00,,"Good morning CAFB team,
I hope my email finds you well. The form to make the request is no longer available which is why I am sending you this email.

CAFB has given our Food pantry a limit of 16,250 pounds per month but we would be grateful if we could have a very higher produce allocation otherwise our distribution will be in trouble. The first reason is that each week we have over 500 guests at our Food distribution (several times we have already exceeded 600 guests!) and the number is only increasing. We have 4 distributions in a month. 16,250 pounds per month is 8 pallets per month. We cannot feed more than 500 people per week with only 8 pallets per month so we will be forced to reduce our distribution to 1 day per month instead of 4 per month. 8 pallets is the minimum number of pallets of food we use for a single distribution in the month. If you look at our order history, for the past several months we have been doing 2 orders per week, one on Tuesday and one on Wednesday in order to have enough produce for all the families that come.

The second reason is that CAFB is our only food supplier. If you maintain the limit of 16,250 pounds per month, the question for us will be: how are we going to get the difference in food that we will no longer have? Having no other suppliers, the only solution will still be to reduce the distribution days.

The third reason is that we do not make our choices based on the pound because we have the space in our Gym to store at least 40 pallets against the wall, if they are pallets stored one on top of the other, that makes us more than 80 and we can also store 12 pallets in our Food pantry room so we have plenty of space to store the food. We make our choices taking into account the diversity of food because of the diversity of cultures who come to take the food.
I hope that all these explanations will make us find favor in your eyes so that you increase our pound limit.

--{adf}{""type"":""expand"",""content"":[{""type"":""paragraph"",""content"":[{""type"":""text"",""text"":""Marie Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours

Hope you had a great Thanksgiving!
We have a concern about the milk that will be delivered to us on Wednesday, December 4 (SO184675). Is it possible that for this time, the amount will be reduced to  *80 cases* instead of 108.

The reason is that at our last milk distribution, we noticed that our guests were very careful about the best by/expiration date and we had milk that was left over. This was not a problem at that time because we were able to keep them in the refrigerator until the following food distribution.
But, we have the same leftover milk, we do not have enough space in the refrigerator at the moment to keep them and we do not want to waste food. This is why we want to be careful.
Thank you in advance for your understanding.

column2: {color:#172B4D}Weâ€™re happy to let you know that weâ€™ve received your order. \\  \\To review the details of your order, including the delivery/pickup date, items ordered, price breakdown, and delivery/pickup time window, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History section inside the Account Overview.{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions, call us at 202-644-9845 or email {color}[{color:#172B4D}partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

{color:#172B4D}Returns: Upon receipt of your order, please ensure that you thoroughly review your order and contact us to report any missing or damaged items immediately. Per our SMART Shopping Training and Agency Agreement, signing for your order upon receipt is confirmation that you have received all products ordered. To review our Return Policy and learn what Capital Area Food Bank considers valid and nonvalid return scenarios, please visit PartnerLink and scroll down to the bottom of the screen for a copy.  \\  \\You will receive an email reminder 24 hours before your order locks in our system. Please remember that your order will close for edits and changes three business days before your delivery/pickup date. If you are having difficulty editing or changing the details of your order, please let us know. \\  *Important for Deliveries:* If the shipping address on your sales order is incorrect, please get in touch with your Regional Coordinator, who will happily assist with ensuring your delivery reaches the correct address on your order date. \\  \\Thank you,  \\  \\The Partner Support Team{color}

Your response on my first request was you will add up produce before my request will be closed. I have no information after then.

I thank you for your usual timely cooperation in this matte. 

Regards, 
Godwin"", ""comment9"": ""08/28/2024 09:56;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Godwin,

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing in response to your recent produce requests, particularly your most recent message. I want to assure you that we do receive all of your produce requests. As we've mentioned before, we can only add produce that is available.

Charity, the Customer Service Coordinator who has been assisting you, explained that we did not have any produce available on Monday. She assured you that she would monitor our inventory and add the produce to your order before it locks *if* it becomes available. Charity kept your ticket open and checked the menu regularly, but unfortunately, we did not have any produce to add to your order before it locked yesterday evening.

I understand your frustration with this process, but please know that the produce we receive is put on the menu as soon as it is available. While my team supports partners by monitoring the menu, it would be best for you to also check the menu for updates. Unfortunately, we cannot add produce that is simply not available.

I hope this provides some clarity. I also double-checked for any available produce before sending this message and saw that none was available.

Thank you,

""D""

Manager of Customer Relations and Distribution Network Evolution (DNE) Â ""}",,0.0

thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""09/18/2024 11:06;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Godwin,

Thank you for your additional ticket. As I mentioned in my last message to you, we only had squash available at the time, which I know you had said your clients don't prefer. I removed it from our order and have been checking the menu since then, but I haven't seen any additional produce available. Even though your order is locked, I will continue to look out for produce today for your agency, as I understand the issues you've had with securing produce for your last two orders. I think it would be helpful for you to meet with Laura and me to discuss this issue further, as it seems to be a recurring problem that is affecting your orders. Can you please let us know some days and times you are available to meet with both Laura and me this week or next week over Zoom?

Thank you for your patience.

column1: Request for 100pcs of Turkey ,PART1-7760,72896,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,uoBt Gnwiuidn,ituGwiBno udn,2024-11-06 10:42:00,2024-11-19 11:00:00,,2024-11-12 08:59:00,,"We are by this mail request Capital Area Foodbank to include in our order for this month 100pcs of Turkey for Thanksgiving, whenever it is available.
Our intention is to have our food give out on Saturday 23rd November 2024 by 12noon
We thank you for your cooperation in this matter.

2404678399",C. C. of C.,Request of Customer Relations,SO184662,DC,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Orders - Pre delivery -> Produce Request,Email Request,English,Order Updated,0.0,,Email to Jira,10440,,service-request,Done,2024-11-12 08:59:00,00:35:07.300000,"{""comment1"": ""11/06/2024 02:35;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon Godwin,

This year, our Food Procurement Team purchased two truckloads of turkeys, each at a cost of approximately $60 to $70 per case and were available on PartnerLink. These turkeys have been allocated to various orders and are no longer available.

I reached out to my colleagues on the Food Resources Team, who informed me that we often receive donated turkeys. These donations will be provided at no cost now that the shared maintenance fee has been waived for donated items. _However_, *we cannot predict if and when these donations will arrive*. Typically, individuals and organizations tend to donate turkeys closer to Thanksgiving, usually in the week before the holiday or during the holiday week itself. 

Please continue to check the menu regularly to see if turkeys are added. If we do receive them, they will be added to the menu and available to partners on a first-come, first-served basis.

Thank you,  
DH"", ""comment2"": ""11/07/2024 01:15;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:5c4638d0-a069-42d1-98e3-db15c053b8ae;Dear Harmon.

Thank you for your response. 

We buy Turkey every year from CAFB in bulk you can check your record. 
I think our organization should have been given some consideration during the sharing of 2 trucks load of Turkey. 

We don't rely on donations we buy our Turkey every year. 

We observed that since Elvis left we have been having issues inrespect of our order, this is very unfair.

Our community are expecting thanksgiving Turkey from us only to disappoint them at the end.

Regards,
Godwin Binutu"", ""comment3"": ""11/07/2024 01:00;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon Godwin, 

  

I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for reaching out to me again regarding the turkey availability. I completely understand how important this is for your community, especially during the holidays. 

  

I want to clarify that all the turkeys we receive are available on a first come, first served basis for all our partners, just like other items on the menu. I also realize that in previous years, there was a fee associated with our donated turkeys (0.19 cents per pound). However, Iâ€™m pleased to share that this fee has been waived for this fiscal year, so itâ€™s possible you may have paid in the past but you would not have to this time for the donated product. 

  

I genuinely want to ensure that you and your clients receive the support you need this holiday season. I understand how quickly these items can disappear from the menu, and I encourage you to check it daily, as we frequently add new products. Right now, we also have vegetable oil, stuffing mix, corn muffin mix, canned collard greens, and beans that might help supplement your holiday distributions. 

  

Please feel free to check the menu regularly, and if I see any additional turkeys come available, I will reach out to you. 

  

Thank you for your understanding, and know that we are here to support you and your community during this important time. 

  

Warm regards,  

""D""{color:#4E8227}{color}

mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]{color:red} so that one of my colleagues or I can assist you promptly. Thank you!{color}{color:red}{color}{color:red}{color}"", ""comment4"": ""11/07/2024 01:26;60f1a20ea211b1006974e353;Hello Godwin,

Iâ€™m sorry to hear that you feel you havenâ€™t gotten the service you would like since there have been changes in staff. I would be happy to connect with you to discuss any challenges you are having. 

Regarding the turkeys, unfortunately, we donâ€™t have the capacity to track every partner that has received turkeys in the past, and it wouldnâ€™t be fair to our other partners to reserve inventory for a select few. However, there are times when we will receive a donation that is specifically allocated for the DC region. While this isnâ€™t a guarantee that we will receive such a donation, nor a promise to reserve anything, the regional team has made note of your interest and will notify you if we receive a special donation of turkeys for the region. As ""D"" mentioned, I also encourage you to continue checking PartnerLink so you will be aware as new items are added.

Please let me know if you have any further questions for the DC regional team. Thank you for your continued partnership and the work you are doing to serve our community.

Best,
Laura

Thank you for your ticket. I have a few updates regarding your request. I was informed this morning that the collard greens and sweet potatoes I had added to your order had to be removed due to quality concerns. As a replacement, I have added two mixed produce pallets to your orderâ€”one as you initially requested and another to compensate for the collard greens and sweet potatoes.  Additionally, we currently do not have any turkeys available for purchase. I see that you already have turkeys in your order, but I do not expect we will be receiving any more turkeys before your order is fulfilled.  

Thank you, and have a great holiday! 

Best,

RE: Important Weather Updates from CAFB ,PART1-8532,81913,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,CH,revenolltihrrcue.p-cmmgo@,rulmpilmcnheocer@trv-.eog,2025-02-11 01:02:00,2025-02-15 01:30:00,,2025-02-11 01:12:00,,"Centreville United Methodist Church is planning to pick up order #SO195586 as scheduled on Thursday morning unless conditions unexpectedly become worse than anticipated. If our plans change, we will let you know.
Deacon, Director of Missions and Communications

We hope you are all doing well. As many of you may know, snowy weather conditions are expected today. The latest forecast indicates that snow will likely begin this afternoon, so we currently plan for all orders scheduled for Tuesday, February 11th, to proceed as originally scheduled.

The most significant weather impact is anticipated on Wednesday, February 12th. As a result, we will be rescheduling or canceling orders for that day in preparation. We encourage partners with orders scheduled for Wednesday to proactively reach out to us at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
column2: mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org] or 202-644-9845 to discuss potential rescheduling. This will help us manage any challenges related to the expected snowfall.  *Please note that delivery dates for Wednesday orders have temporarily been changed to February 28th until we can confirm new delivery dates with each partner.*

column1: For partners with orders scheduled for the rest of the week, including Wednesday, Thursday, or Friday, we appreciate your communication regarding any plans to delay or cancel your orders. Effective communication is crucial for prioritizing the safety of both our team and yours. Together, we can navigate this snowy weather safely and efficiently.
We will keep you updated on any final decisions made by our Operations and Leadership Teams regarding delays or closures.
Thank you for your understanding and partnership. If you have any questions or concerns, please donâ€™t hesitate to reach out.

Customer Relations",C. column1: Error with Delivery for SO186461 ,PART1-8235,79137,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,islum@ihtacebroyecgmnor.,atikAc rusguFe,2025-01-10 09:18:00,2025-01-17 01:30:00,,2025-01-13 01:10:00,,"Good morning Lisa,

Did you communicate these errors to CAFB Partner Support on 12/3/2024? If not, I recommend doing so in the future at the time when you figure out any errors with an order. The Parter Support team members are wizards and can fix almost anything related to PartnerLink or deliveries! I am CCing them on this email to start a help ticket for [SO186461

As I understand it, you have been overcharged for several items because you didnâ€™t actually receive the number of cases reflected on the Sales Order (Spaghetti, black beans, milk). [@Partner Support
column2: mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org] could you all please process a refund for these items?

column1: Regarding the  +extra+ cases delivered, I am not an expert on what to do, so Iâ€™ll let Partner Support weigh in.
*Cc:* Kent Sovine <kent@communitycheer.org>; Vanesa Pinto <vanesa@communitycheer.org>; Karla Castro <karla@communitycheer.org>

The tables below show the errors in December's delivery. You can also see the delivery ticket attached where I made note of the actual number of boxes received of items we ordered, as well as extra items we received.
We assume that there was just a mix-up of the pallets upon unloading of the truck.
Will our account balance remain at $2,132.72, based on the original order?

Lisa",C.,Request of Customer Relations,SO186461 ,VA,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Delivery / Pickup -> Report Issue,Email Request,English,Question Answered,0.0,,Email to Jira,10440,04:08:00,service-request,Done,2025-01-13 01:10:00,00:52:28.100000,"{""comment1"": ""01/10/2025 10:14;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:87a3b151-e984-4fdd-9258-8be7a9ccde58;Hi Augusta,

No, we did not communicate the errors on 12/3. Thank you for the guidance in the event of future situations. 

Kindly,
Lisa"", ""comment2"": ""01/10/2025 02:52;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to us regarding the issues you encountered with your order. Our Return Policy, which is covered in our SMART Shopping Training, informs partners that any order discrepancies must be reported immediately. We provide partners with 24 hours for perishable items and 72 hours for non-perishable items to notify us about returns, exchanges, or any issues with their orders. We also encourage all partners to thoroughly review their orders upon delivery or pickup, so they can inform us about any discrepancies as soon as possible. I understand that circumstances, such as delivery day events, holidays, and our holiday and snow closures, can sometimes disrupt this process which can acount in the delay in notification.

Unfortunately, since the items you did not order have already been distributed and we are now beyond the timeframe for reporting discrepancies, the original account balance you paid for the order remains unchanged. We sincerely apologize for the inconvenience this has caused your agency, especially regarding not receiving all the items you ordered. 

In the future, if you experience any issues like this, please contact my team, the Customer Relations Team, immediately via email at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
column2:
mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]. This will automatically create a ticket for my team. You can also reach us at our shared phone number 202-644-9845.

Thank you,

DH  
Manager of Customer Relations and Distribution Network Evolution"", ""comment3"": ""01/13/2025 02:34;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:87a3b151-e984-4fdd-9258-8be7a9ccde58;Thank you, ""D"", for your response.

I am copying our food distribution team, and we will be sure to immediately report to your Customer Relations Team any discrepancies we may encounter in the future.

Kind regards,

Lisa BÃ¼ttner"", ""comment4"": ""01/13/2025 02:34;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.""}",,0.0

column1: I hope this message finds you well. I am excited to announce the Children of Mine Youth Center has welcomed Nicole Lloyd as our new Community Outreach and Food Distribution Coordinator.

To ensure Nicole can effectively contribute to our programs, it is vital that she undergoes training with the Food Bank. This training will equip her with the necessary knowledge and resources to assist in our food distribution and community outreach program.
Could you please add Nicole to the schedule for the next available training session?
Please let me know if you have any questions or need further information. Your assistance in this process is greatly appreciated.
I've added this message to our organization's letterhead. See attachment.

column1: Donâ€™t ever hesitate to reach out about incorrect orders, even if itâ€™s just a minor mistake. We want to be sure our inventory is always correct, so it helps to have partners let us know when weâ€™ve made a mistake.

{color:#172B4D}I just came back from vacation yesterday and was looking over our inventory to compose our guidelines for this week and noticed that the chicken that we received on Friday was not the TEFAP chicken that we had ordered for pick up on 11/08.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}It's on our team for not checking properly the case size and weight but the chicken which we received was the following:{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}300595 Chicken Leg Quarters, Halal 5# Chicken Leg Quarters, Halal 5# 6/5 lbs Bag{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}We received 9 cases of the above chicken. I knew it wasn't correct based on the count and the fact that it was halal. I believe this is a purchase item through the CAFB website and wanted to check with you and the team to see how you would like to proceed.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}As a side note, on a past order we received 6 cases of TEFAP red kidney beans instead we had ordered 6 cases of TEFAP pears which was a minor problem and explained the importance of checking the order with our team prior to accepting.{color}

""D"" "", ""comment3"": ""11/19/2024 11:33;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning, Maria,  

Thank you for bringing this issue to our attention. I appreciate your prompt reporting. We have informed our Operations Team about the matter, and they are currently calibrating our inventory to address it internally.  Please follow Joanna's guidance on how to report only what you actually received. We will take care of the necessary items on our end. In the future, if similar instances occur, please make sure to review your order thoroughly upon delivery. If you notice any discrepancies, contact us immediately at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org so we can escalate the issue to our Operations Team as soon as possible. 

Thank you for your cooperation.  
Best regards,

Fw: Damaged food ,PART1-8640,82935,[System] Service request,Completed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,Knnnlgi Aaa,gnnKlaa iAn,2025-02-24 09:51:00,2025-02-26 08:14:00,,2025-02-25 07:08:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hi ""D"",{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Passing this along directly to you as we have received quite a few complaints about the canned peaches. Did you ever hear back from the Warehouse about if they have been able to check the rest of the boxes? Also are you all able to connect with Emily directly about her refund request?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

We received a delivery of food on Tuesday, February 18. Everything was fine except for one case of peaches. 17 cans out of 24 in the case were damaged. I have pictures below. The cans with the black spots are holes where the juice leaked out. The two cans on paper had leaked and were stuck to the paper. You can see all the cans that were wet. We cannot give out food that is stained like this; plus, we have no way of knowing if the contents are bad. We could use only 7 cans from this box. Since prices are so much higher now and our money is tighter, we would like a refund.
I have not heard anything about the cans of pears that were damaged a few weeks ago.
Emily Ewing  West End Food Pantry. PS: ignore the last picture of drills; I donâ€™t know how to delete it!

I hope all is well with you. I was reaching out regards to order number SO171842. I wanted to know did you all have any produce available for a delivery on August 23rd?
On Thu, Aug 8, 2024, 3:42 PM Michelle Limes <[mdlimes1@gmail.com
Subject: Capital Area Food Bank Order- SO171842

column2: {color:#172B4D}Weâ€™re happy to let you know that weâ€™ve received your order. \\  \\To review the details of your order, including the delivery/pickup date, items ordered, price breakdown, and delivery/pickup time window, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History section inside the Account Overview.{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions, call us at 202-644-9845 or email {color}[{color:#172B4D}partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

{color:#172B4D}Returns: Upon receipt of your order, please ensure that you thoroughly review your order and contact us to report any missing or damaged items immediately. Per our SMART Shopping Training and Agency Agreement, signing for your order upon receipt is confirmation that you have received all products ordered. To review our Return Policy and learn what Capital Area Food Bank considers valid and nonvalid return scenarios, please visit PartnerLink and scroll down to the bottom of the screen for a copy.  \\  \\You will receive an email reminder 24 hours before your order locks in our system. Please remember that your order will close for edits and changes three business days before your delivery/pickup date. If you are having difficulty editing or changing the details of your order, please let us know. \\  *Important for Deliveries:* If the shipping address on your sales order is incorrect, please get in touch with your Regional Coordinator, who will happily assist with ensuring your delivery reaches the correct address on your order date. \\  \\Thank you,  \\  \\The Partner Support Team{color}

column2: {color:#172B4D}Weâ€™re happy to let you know that weâ€™ve received your order. \\  \\ To review the details of your order, including the delivery/pickup date, items ordered, price breakdown, and delivery/pickup time window, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History section inside the Account Overview.{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions, call us at 202-644-9845 or email {color}[{color:#172B4D}partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

{color:#172B4D}Returns: Upon receipt of your order, please ensure that you thoroughly review your order and contact us to report any missing or damaged items immediately. Per our SMART Shopping Training and Agency Agreement, signing for your order upon receipt is confirmation that you have received all products ordered. To review our Return Policy and learn what Capital Area Food Bank considers valid and nonvalid return scenarios, please visit PartnerLink and scroll down to the bottom of the screen for a copy.  \\  \\ You will receive an email reminder 24 hours before your order locks in our system. Please remember that your order will close for edits and changes three business days before your delivery/pickup date. If you are having difficulty editing or changing the details of your order, please let us know. \\  *Important for Deliveries:* If the shipping address on your sales order is incorrect, please get in touch with your Regional Coordinator, who will happily assist with ensuring your delivery reaches the correct address on your order date. \\  \\ Thank you,  \\  \\ The Partner Support Team{color}

{color:#172B4D}*Subject:* Reminder for Mandatory Hours of Operations Training (One Training Remaining!){color}

If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use.
Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on  {color:#e03e2d}*September 19th from 9 am to 10 am*.{color} These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to [register
column2: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u]your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations.

column1: While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.

I tried to checkout a couple of times and got the same message. I tried logging out and logging back in. When I logged back in the cart symbol at the top right was in the process of being emptied it was counting down. Which I thought was a good thing because when you actually get to place the order it does that usually. But once it was done counting down there wasn't a new sales order. I didn't check yet but I assume the time slot I had is no longer available for delivery? Do I just have to start all over and pick a different delivery day and time? Will I still need to do it in two orders and provide you with the two sales order numbers so you can change it to the same day and time? We usually use the invoice option when checking out but it wasn't available so we used the debit card. Once someone from your end took a bunch of items out the invoice option was available. So if this is something you can do from your end you wouldn't need the CC info you could just choose the invoice option for each order and set it up for this Thursday. Please advise.

I do apologize for all this back and forth that we have had a to do to solve for these issues. I spoke to our IT Department this morning and wanted to relay some of the information that we discussed. First, the reason that you are unable to invoice your orders is because your agency has a balance over 90 days which means that your invoicing capabilities have been removed. Your agencyâ€™s balance is $2,254.84. Until this amount is paid off, we will not be able to invoice any of your orders. Secondly, because we are unable to invoice your orders. We internally cannot place an order for you because we don't have access to your card information. I confirmed with our IT Team that the max number of items that PartnerLink will allow you to check out with is 21. The quantities do not play a factor into this, just the number of items themselves. If you are able to, please check out and place two orders to ensure you get all your items by place two orders that have 21 items. For reference, this is an issue that our IT Team is currently working on fixing so that we do not have to do this continuously. 

Please let me know if you have any questions. Again, I do apologize for the inconvenience. 

If you have questions about this, please feel free to give me a call at 571-390-9875

P.,Request of Customer Relations,none,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Agency Administration -> Connection to CAFB Staff,Grant Support,English,Connected to CAFB Staff,4.0,2024-09-16 12:45:00,Portal,10800,12:38:00,service-request,Done,2024-09-16 12:21:00,00:18:03.400000,"{""comment1"": ""09/16/2024 12:18;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon Partner,

Thank you for your inquiry about Capacity Grants. We do indeed offer Capacity Grants at Capital Area Food Bank intended to help our partners expand their operations by providing financial assistance to cover the cost of items like storage or a vehicle. The Capacity Grant Application is embedded in our 2024 Fall Bi-Annual Survey, which will be released to partners in the second week of October. Please note that you will need to open and fill out the survey to access the Capacity Grant Application and then submit it. Once you submit your application, it will be reviewed by your Regional Team for consideration.

Thank you,

Customer Relations"", ""comment2"": ""09/16/2024 12:19;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Please also reach out to your Regional Team Members to learn more about external grant opportunities that may be available for support.""}",,0.0

column1: Re: Reminder for Mandatory Hours of Operations Training (One Training Remaining!) ,PART1-7416,68537,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,o-u.iesmsievsn@amtct.etensty,@nt-caevus.stsnmsy.teieitoem,2024-09-13 05:24:00,2024-09-20 01:30:00,,2024-09-14 01:36:00,,"I have already attended this training. Angela Wilson at Crossover Church. The very first training I was on line.
Angela Wilson sent from my iPhone

If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use.
Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on  {color:#e03e2d}*September 19th from 9 am to 10 am*{color}{color:#e03e2d}.{color} These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to [register
column2: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u]your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations.

column1: While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.

The Customer Relations Team {quote}",C. Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders ,PART1-8211,78952,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,ie.@tnyt-sssinmoe.vcmaeutste,msiu.nea.etteicstysnt-@mvoes,2025-01-08 10:23:00,2025-01-12 01:30:00,,2025-01-08 11:57:00,,"Hello
Can you please cancel my order and I will do a new one. Thank you. Angela Wilson from Crossover Church. My order was for Wednesday Jan 8th at 10:00 am today.
Angela Wilson sent from my iPhone

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th.

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

Customer Relations{quote}",C. CiArra"", ""comment4"": ""07/03/2024 01:12;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for contacting us about this issue. Unfortunately, there is a limit to the number of cases available for this item, and we are unable to provide more than 15 cases. Some of our items have case limits, especially produce and protein. These limits are in place to ensure that the product is available in a fair manner so that our partners can take advantage of it.

If you have any further questions, please feel free to ask.

Below is the list of produce items in your order *SO195653*:

* 700757 Produce Pallet - 3 WAY - Cabbage, Carrot, Sweet Potatoes  - Qty 2
* 800111 Apples, Local Cardboard Bin 700# AVG - Qty 1

Please respond to this email with your selections of which produce item you would like us to reduce. Kindly note that if we do not receive your response within 24 hours, our Customer Relations team will make adjustments to your order on your behalf.

Thank you for your attention to this matter!

Best regards,

Thank you for contacting customer support. If you are having any issues editing your order please contact customer support as soon as possible and we are happy to make the changes for you as we do not recommend creating multiple orders and please keep in mind that all orders lock 3 business days before your scheduled pick-up or delivery date. Both SO186448 and SO186453 are locked for edits. I will look into what we can do to combine your orders for 11/27 and if possible to add the order for 12/02. 

Charity"", ""comment2"": ""11/25/2024 11:13;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:1ecfe059-a1f8-4eb4-9014-624ee8f0fc50;That would be great, thank you!"", ""comment3"": ""11/25/2024 02:12;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning,

I hope this message finds you well! I wanted to reach out regarding your request. I have combined everything for your order tomorrow into SO185606. 

Going forward, please contact us by phone or email before creating multiple orders. The reason we do not combine orders is that, systematically, it can cause issues. It makes it difficult to manage produce on orders and can lead to losing items due to backorders.

Additionally, please be aware that with the new produce limits we are introducing, partners will need to wait 30 minutes after placing an order to edit it. Moreover, there will be another 30-minute waiting period after making any edits before further changes can be made.

We appreciate your patience as we navigate this change.

Thank you!

Best,

Good afternoon,

I hope this message finds you well. I'm reaching out to address the deer meat that you ordered a few weeks ago. One of my team members informed me about the issue, and we've been in touch with our Operations Department. They initially located the meat in the warehouse, but upon further attempts, they couldn't find it, as we are preparing for inventory. We apologize for the inconvenience and any confusion caused by the back and forth communication.

I've processed a courtesy credit of $15.20 for the total amount of the cases. Once approved by our Finance Department, this credit will be applied to Invoice 161606.

Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions or concerns.

Thank you,
