column1: Re: Memorial Day 5/27 ,PART1-6556,56499,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,xbRac cTeea,Tc aeRcexba,2024-05-13 04:37:00,2024-05-18 01:31:00,,2024-05-14 10:49:00,,"Yes! tuesday the 28th in the earliest slot please! Thank you so much.
On Mon, May 13, 2024 at 16:10 Partner Support <[partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused.

Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule.

In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding.
Thank you for your patience and cooperation.
{color:#4e8227}Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution{color}{color:#4e8227}{color}

Thank you for contacting Customer Support. Please note that even if you are a TEFAP partner, partners will be charged a delivery fee if there is non-TEFAP products on their order. SO180247 AND SO180435 both include non-TEFAP products and were assigned our standard delivery fee of $75. I am unsure why the delivery charge was added to SO180174, and will look into getting it removed. 

If you would like to keep your deliveries free of charge moving forward, please make sure your order contains TEFAP products only.

column1: Question about September and October delivery orders ,PART1-7736,72573,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,nm@nrrgtsozal.nevoie,lorraeg@ntsneno.vmiz,2024-11-01 03:19:00,2024-11-08 01:30:00,,2024-11-04 09:25:00,,"Hello, this inquiry relates to maintaining inventory reports for food delivery and distribution at the Ebenezer Baptist Church in Woodbridge, Virginia. After reviewing the records, we received an order on September 27, 2024, and only received a copy of the delivery sheet page one. However, on the page it is note as page one of two. We did not observe a page two. We would like a copy of page two for our inventory records. IF it is possible an emailed copy would be helpful.

Also, the delivery reports for September 27, 2024, and October 25, 2024, document the delivery of item 540184 (VA-TEFAP Canned, Beef Stew 24oz 24.24oz Case. Both deliveries were not cans of beef stew but beef stew pouches (item 540073). Our inquiry is for having the correct item numbers and product listed on our inventory reports.

If you can respond to this email message with a copy of the page two delivery document for the delivery September 27, 224 and share instructions for coding the inventory reports regarding the Beef stew (cans versus pouches) for the months of September and October, it would be appreciated.

*Subject:* [EXTERNAL] Change in Your Upcoming Sales Order{color}
{color:#FF0000}[Note: This email originated from outside of the organization. Do not click links or open attachments unless you recognize the sender and know the content is safe.]{color}

We regret to inform you that we had to remove or reduce the quantity of item(s) from your order  *SO182767*. Below is a list of item(s) and reason for the change. We understand that this change may cause inconvenience to you and your distribution plans, and we apologize for the inconvenience. Please note that if you are receiving this notification after your order has been locked, which is three business days before your order is due to be picked up or delivered, this change is most likely occurring during or after the pulling stage and unfortunately, we cannot replace the item removed or make any further additions during this time period.

To review an updated version of your order, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History tab. If you have any queries or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
Thank you for your understanding and continued support.

Thank you"", ""comment4"": ""10/09/2024 12:15;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon

Thank you for contacting us about food item dates and quality issues. We want to ensure that all the food leaving our warehouse is safe for consumption and properly dated for your knowledge. Some of the items you mentioned are *donated products*. As we increase the donated products on our menu, I want to make sure that all partners are aware that Capital Area Food Bank accepts donations with items past their best by and sell by dates.

The best by date is an indicator of the quality of a product but is not a safety date. The sell by date is for inventory management and tells the store for how long to display the product for sale. The product can still be consumed after this date. It's important to note that many of our donated products will be past these dates, but they are not expired and are still safe for consumption.

We have food coding guides that partners can print and reference during distributions. When available, they can be ordered in English and Spanish from our Nutrition Education Department. The dates on some products may cause concerns for partners and their clients, but we urge you all to differentiate between the different dates on products, use the food coding guide as a reference, and also use your best judgment as well as your food safety knowledge. If you have a product that is not of the right consistency, has an odor, or you believe to be not okay, please let us know and discard the item immediately. As we increase our donations, we may encounter some challenges, but please work with us and continue to provide us with feedback.

Additionally, if you ever have an issue with fresh produce, please include photos of the items so that we can forward them to our Operations and Food Resourcing Departments for their knowledge.

We appreciate your partnership with us in this.

For Nutrition Materials including the Food Coding Guide, please email: [education@capitalareafoodbank.org

column1: Wrong items delivered ,PART1-6714,58826,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,auaKlhnchoM a,chMuhln aoaKa,2024-06-05 11:19:00,2024-07-01 11:55:00,,2024-06-13 05:27:00,,"{color:#172b4d}Hello there,{color}
{color:#172b4d}Our volunteers just picked up some of the items from your warehouse. I have ordered 3 boxes of oatmeal but we received 3 boxes or rice instead.{color}
{color:#172b4d}Can we return them and get the oatmeal that we ordered in the first place?{color}{color:#172b4d}{color}
{color:#172b4d}Thank you very much for your great help and support!{color}

Capital Area Food Bank"", ""comment2"": ""06/05/2024 01:33;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon, 

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. I am working on identifying what happened here with the mixup of items, as you are not the only partner with a similar issue with these products. I will provide you with more information when I have it. 

Thank you, 

""D"" "", ""comment3"": ""06/05/2024 01:35;712020:8e94303c-4df5-4aac-bf25-fd34e07c5244;Thank you very much ""D"" for your great support. I will be waiting to hear back from you."", ""comment4"": ""06/05/2024 04:57;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for your patience while I figured this out for you. We have identified a labeling error and appreciate your help in bringing it to our attention. We have initiated the process of resolving this issue, yet we have identified that we do not have oatmeal in inventory at this time. If you would like to return the product you received, please do, and we will process that return for you. We do apologize for this mix-up.

Thank you,

""D"""", ""comment5"": ""06/05/2024 06:50;712020:8e94303c-4df5-4aac-bf25-fd34e07c5244;Thank you ""D"",

Yes we would like to return the items (3 boxes). Can we do this on Wednesday 6/12 during our pick up time? 

Thanks again

Manal"", ""comment6"": ""06/05/2024 08:16;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Yes, you can return the items during your next pickup. Please inform the warehouse associate assisting you that you are returning the product and have already spoken to Customer Service. Thank you!{color:#4E8227}{color}

MOCO grant,PART1-4886,54365,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,rPn dayCaeon, aaPConrnyed,2024-04-26 01:11:00,2024-05-03 01:33:00,,2024-04-29 08:59:00,,"Dear partner support coordinator, we at FBC Ken-Gar have grant allocations from 3 different grants, 2 of the expires in 30 days and the third expires in June. When we order food the funds are taken out of the grant that expires later. Is there any way that you could take the money from the accounts that expire first. It would be greatly appreciated. Thanks! FBC coordinator.{adf}{""type"":""expand"",""content"":[{""type"":""paragraph"",""content"":[{""type"":""text"",""text"":""Sent from my T-Mobile 5G Device""},{""type"":""hardBreak""},{""type"":""text"",""text"":""Get ""},{""type"":""text"",""text"":""Outlook for Android"",""marks"":[{""type"":""link"",""attrs"":{""href"":""https://aka.ms/AAb9ysg""}}]}]}],""attrs"":{""title"":""Signature""}}{adf}",FBC K.,Partner Knowledge/Training,SO157471 ,,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Billing / Grants -> Grant Support,Email Request,English,Issue Resolved (ERP/Accounting),0.0,,Email to Jira,9780,12:11:00,service-request,Done,2024-04-29 08:59:00,00:49:20.800000,"{""comment1"": ""04/26/2024 03:49;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for contacting our Customer Service. I'd be happy to assist you with your query.

Our system applies grants on a per-line-item basis, meaning only one grant can be applied to each line item. In your past couple of orders, you have had line items with high numbers ranging from $250 to $2,653.30. Â The system is going to use the grant that has enough available funds which might not be the one with the closest expiration date. Please see below: 

You have three grants:

* 1-G $3,000 (Expires 1^st^)
** SO136067 used $890.00
** SO122558 used $812.60
*** Remaining Balance: $514.98
* 1-H $2,378 (Expires 2^nd^)
** SO146902 used $762.58
** SO142621 used $1,498.84
*** Remaining Balance: $116.58
* 1-I $6,564 (Expires 3^rd^)
** *SO157471 (your most recent order)* _was placed and totaled in $854.20, the only grant that could cover the entirety of this line item for the chicken was your 1-I grant. If the system pulled from either of your other two grants, it would not cover the total cost of the chicken._

I hope this clarifies the situation. If you have any more questions, please feel free to ask.

Best regards,

FISH of Laurel is so very happy to receive this $6006.85 grant as it has been many years since we have received a grant from CAFB!

I have a question about invoice #194073 (this orderÂ #SO192982 was received on 2/13; it was originally scheduled for delivery on 2/10, but there was a problem that day and the driver failed to arrive during the 8:00-10:00 AM delivery window).
On 2/14, we received the following email:

{color:#ff5630}We are delighted to inform you that your organization has been awardedÂ grantÂ funding to support your efforts in addressing food security in our community.Â {color}{color:#ff5630}*$6,006.85*{color}{color:#ff5630}Â has been awarded to your organization under the new food creditÂ grantÂ â€“Â FY25 Maryland DHSÂ and the funds were made available in your account onÂ Monday,Â February 10th, 2025. Partner food credits can be used by your organization toÂ purchaseÂ grantÂ eligible items using CAFBâ€™s Partner Link Menu.Â Â {color}

{color:#ff5630}Your partner food creditÂ grantÂ deadline is May 15th, 2025. Please remember that the food creditÂ grantÂ deadline is applied to the delivery or pick up scheduled date, not the date you placed the order. CAFB reserves the right to change deadlines and to reallocate and/or extendÂ grantÂ deadlines based on partner usage to ensure contract requirements are being met. If your organization cannot use the fullÂ grantÂ amount before the deadline, please tell us as soon as possible.Â Â Â Â Â {color}{color:#fff0b3}Â {color}
Are you able to apply the grant to this order? I believe that a number of items on this order are grant designated.

Charity "", ""comment2"": ""02/25/2025 01:35;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon!

Thank you for submitting your inquiry. I have contacted the Maryland Regional Team and reviewed the documentation provided for the grant. Unfortunately, the grant can only be applied to orders with a creation date after February 10th, which is when the funds were uploaded to your accounts. Therefore, we cannot apply the grant to any orders created before February 10th, even if they were delivered after that date.

If you have any questions, please let me know.

Best,

column1: RE: FLCC/Crowder Owens Food Bank: Account Set up and Access for Eric Ray ,PART1-8262,79435,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,rBEinnorw ,nEnrorw iB,2025-01-13 02:46:00,2025-01-21 10:20:00,,2025-01-13 04:27:00,,"Hello Eric,
Here is the link to register for our CAFB Smart Shopping Training with our Customer Relations Team: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/smart-shopping-training-md-dc-
There are 2 trainings offered each month. You can register for the time that is most convenient for you.
Please reach out to me or Partner Support at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
column2: mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org] if you have any questions about the training.

column1: {color:#4E8227}4900 Puerto Rico Avenue NE, Washington, DC 20017{color}
*Subject:* Re: FLCC/Crowder Owens Food Bank: Account Set up and Access for Eric Ray
If it's the same one I got from Zaynab (spelling??) Then I haven't been getting them.
The only mobile distribution request was from you when we met. Nothing before that. It most likely went to Carrie.
Erin, I look forward to hearing from you.

{color:#172B4D}Thank you so much for reaching out. I've added our DC coordinator, Erin Brown here who can assist you with signing up for SMART shopping training. Could you confirm you've been receiving the monthly report to record the data for the mobile distributions? If you could send me the date for the next one, that would be great.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}Should you need anything else, please let me know.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
*Subject:* FLCC/Crowder Owens Food Bank: Account Set up and Access for Eric Ray{color}

I'm returning from the holidays and the snow . We are in transition and as you may know Carrie is no longer with FLCC/Crowder Owens Food Bank. column1: Fw: Change in contact information ,PART1-7007,63852,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,Alna nKiagn,Aln igaKann,2024-07-29 07:25:00,2024-08-02 01:30:00,,2024-07-29 08:27:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hi Everyone!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I just wanted to follow up on the email below, can you all please update the main contact for Floris UMC to be Katie Rakestraw?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Sorry for so many emails today, lots of partners are requesting changes in contacts right now! Can you all please make Katie the new main contact? it is saying she does not have the password associated with the email?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

Hi Alanna - It was good to see you today. As Donna mentioned, our agency contact info is changing. Donna and I will continue to be the day-to-day contacts and need to receive copies of any and all communications from CAFB to ensure you get any necessary response from Floris.
Shell Lewis, the Director of Serve Ministries, will vacate her role next week. The position had not yet been filled.

Allan Ballenger has retired as the Executive Director. As of yesterday, Barbara Miner (bminer@florisumc.org) is now our Executive Pastor. Though she will probably be the one who signs the partner agreement, she has no involvement in the day to day operation of our food distribution program and would prefer not to receive routine emails from CAFB.
If you need us to complete a form, please let me know.

Capital Area Food Bank"", ""comment3"": ""05/29/2024 11:15;712020:b15fa988-bc60-49b4-aa6f-e30b7a3629c1;Good morning,

Thank you for contacting customer support. The food bank has announced closures on June 7th for an all-staff outing, and June 27th and 28th for an Inventory Blackout. While the food bank will be closed on the 4th of July, this will not cause any interruptions on July 5th. We will be open and operating at our normal capacity. Please keep in mind that holidays are not considered a business day, so orders scheduled on July 5th will lock a day earlier to honor our 3 business day rule for locking orders. 

All updates for holiday and staff closings can be found on the main landing page on Partnerlink.

Charity""}",,0.0

Re: Rescheduling your order ,PART1-8189,78754,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,b.tydcilmtg.omoufyprcgfman@toootago,nmogt.ogfrmpdagoyto.cott@cbfiyoamul,2025-01-07 02:31:00,2025-01-12 01:30:00,,2025-01-08 02:25:00,2025-01-08 12:00:00,"Hello,

Thank you for reaching out. If the order could be rescheduled to a time later this week that would be great. We are having a pantry this Saturday and we are running low on oil, produce and meats as this is part of the order. Iâ€™m actually out of town this his week so could you please reach out to Christian Pfeffer-Kleemann, his number is +1 (507) 316-4048. I also included him in the distribution list of this email.

If there is no option to reschedule for this week, can you please reschedule the order to January 24th 10 a.m.? In this case please remove the produce from the order if you canâ€™t hold it safely at the food bank.
Thank you for your support of our community
{color:#172B4D} I hope this email finds you well. Due to the inclement weather and the resulting closure of our operations today, we are unable to process orders as scheduled.

We kindly ask if you would like to reschedule your order for some time next week to please respond to this email. Please contact us at your earliest convenience to let us know your preferred date and time for rescheduling or if you would prefer us to cancel your order.{color}

{color:#172B4D} We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding and cooperation. If you have any questions or need further assistance, please do not hesitate to reach out. Thank you for your attention to this matter, and we look forward to hearing from you soon.{color}

thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""01/07/2025 05:41;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for your message. I understand the urgency of your order, especially given the current needs of our clients. I have escalated this issue to my team in the Operations Department, who will be back at work tomorrow. We will do our best to fulfill your order as quickly as possible. 

I will follow up with you tomorrow to provide an update on your order.

Thank you!  
""D"""", ""comment3"": ""01/08/2025 09:25;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:7718867a-2bc4-48d8-9623-2d74d57fb249;Hello ""D"",

Best regards,

column1: FW: Weevils  ,PART1-7294,67197,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,CR,CR,2024-08-29 03:13:00,2024-09-07 01:32:00,,2024-09-03 10:27:00,,"Hi All,
We just got a report from a Virginia partner, Food For Others, that masa flour they received from us on 8/6 had weevils in it. Please see order details below:
* Item Code: 300256 Corn Flour, Masa Harina Minsa
Have we received this report from other VA partners? Can we check the remaining supply we have to ensure it is weevil free?

I hate to bother you with such a pesky problem but the Maseca we purchased on 8/6/2024 has a weevil infestation. I wanted you to be aware but I also want to make sure the remaining Maseca on the menu is pest free. We will need to replace our stock, should I find another source temporarily?
April Frazier Simmons â€¢ Director of Operations & Client Services

Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders ,PART1-8194,78759,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,mvtss@.iscaeneuttoyetms-ine.,ot.mti@ssatsne-uec.nitemsevy,2025-01-07 04:02:00,2025-01-11 01:30:00,,2025-01-07 04:15:00,,"Good day,
I hope this finds you well.
Is it possible to reschedule SO189181
If not please cancel the order.

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th.

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

Customer Relations{quote}",F. Of D. C. Re: Issue with Food Assistance Delivery from Gaithersburg HELP ,PART1-7845,73662,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,rdgphtegarohgir@slenmum.grgaa.bloo,@.rrgamga.uonstgeghredrlaopmbloigh,2024-11-14 05:37:00,2024-11-23 01:30:00,,2024-11-19 09:56:00,,"Ms. Jackson,

Gaithersburg HELP is an all-volunteer organization that has been serving the needy in our local community for 56 years, and we are dedicated to supporting as many families with food each month as we can. In fact, last month HELP served 500 families at our pantry in the Festival Shopping Center. We have only a couple of volunteer drivers who can deliver food, and we must reserve that service for those individuals who live alone or have a partner who also can't drive to the pantry. You had asked for us to deliver food to a family of 9 people. As you must know from your previous food pickups, which total 30 since 2018, we pack according to family size; so a family of 9 would receive at least 8 heavy bags of groceries. We simply can't ask a volunteer, all of whom tend to be over 60 years of age, to pick up and deliver many bags of groceries; and that would not be appropriate when there are able-bodied family members in residence. As an all-volunteer organization, we strive to serve as many families as possible; but we can sustain our operation only if almost all of our families pick up at the pantry. If a client needs to come to the pantry via bus, we offer bus tokens so that transportation to and from the pantry is free.

It is not an insult to let someone know that we have limited capabilities for food delivery. It's just a fact. And we would not ask to see proof of disability. We explain our limited delivery ability to any client who asks about delivery. Also, our coordinators always provide information about how to get food from Manna and/or the Gaithersburg Hope Center. Clients can get food from us while also getting food from those other organizations. In that way, we hope clients find they have more money to apply toward rent or utility bills. Our yearly client survey results validate that outcome and that our volunteers treat clients with dignity and promptness.
We could serve your family very quickly with food if someone could drive to the pantry or come via bus.
On Thu, Nov 14, 2024 at 2:11â€¯PM 'Yvette Jackson' via Info <[info@gaithersburghelp.org
Dear Capital Area Food Bank Support Team,
My name is Yvette Jackson, and I am writing to report an issue I experienced with food assistance delivery from Gaithersburg HELP.

On Monday at 9:36 a.m., I called to apply for food assistance delivery, but my request was refused based on the number of people in my household and our ages. Specifically, this refusal has caused significant inconveniences and insult to my family and me, as we urgently need food assistance. Insulting my family by indicating ""With such a large family someone should be able to take the bus here for pick up!"" shows a lack of empathy and compassion. After making a complaint, I received a response at 12:54 p.m. today, indicating that the refusal and statement were correct due to the volunteer nature of the service and their inability to deliver help to a large household. I was directed to seek assistance from other sources such as Manna Food.

I believe there might be a misunderstanding or miscommunication regarding our eligibility for this service. Attached to this email, you will find documentation of my disability for your review. Please note the MetroAccess document on line 16, which indicates that my disability prevents me from independently using the accessible Metrobus and Metrorail system for all trips. I am unable to walk due to L spine disease with a risk of falls, panic attacks, anxiety, and non-tolerance to crowds. At this point, I feel my disability, age, and household circumstances are severely limiting my access to essential help.

I would appreciate your assistance in reviewing this matter and providing any necessary support to ensure that my household can receive the food assistance we need as it appears Gaithersburg Help is not completely meeting the needs of the community. I value your prompt attention to this issue and look forward to your response.

Somehow, your family managed to pick up food at the pantry many times. \n\nMargo{adf}{\""type\"":\""expand\"",\""content\"":[{\""type\"":\""paragraph\"",\""content\"":[{\""type\"":\""text\"",\""text\"":\""Margo Goldman \""},{\""type\"":\""hardBreak\""},{\""type\"":\""text\"",\""text\"":\""Executive Director, Gaithersburg HELP  \""},{\""type\"":\""hardBreak\""},{\""type\"":\""text\"",\""text\"":\""margo.goldman@gaithersburghelp.org\"",\""marks\"":[{\""type\"":\""link\"",\""attrs\"":{\""href\"":\""mailto:margo.goldman@gaithersburghelp.org\""}}]}]}],\""attrs\"":{\""title\"":\""Signature\""}}{adf}"", ""comment4"": ""11/14/2024 06:07;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:90e5acb6-fb65-404d-a8b3-9704879b6a5d;
column15:
{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}"", ""comment5"": ""11/14/2024 06:23;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:58d15b4c-6d52-447e-947b-3e7da2bb2a2a;We were able to pick up when I had a vehicle but there have been times when delivery was accommodated before having transportation, around 2018.

Just so you are aware, working doesn't automatically mean someone is able-bodied. ""Able-bodied"" typically refers to a person who has no physical disabilities and can perform tasks without any limitations caused by a disability. Many people with disabilities or health conditions can still work, often with the help of accommodations or support.

So, just because someone has a job, it doesn't necessarily mean they don't have a disability. It's important to look at each person's unique situation and disabilities which you have indicated is not asked. 

Thank you for your response. This ends our conversation, however, I have added other agencies in this correspondence just so they are aware.


Best regards,{color:#26282a}{color}{adf}{""type"":""expand"",""content"":[{""type"":""paragraph"",""content"":[{""type"":""text"",""text"":""Ms. Yvette L. Thank you for contacting customer support. I am looking into the dates for your previous orders to confirm that they are safe to eat. 

As a reference, feel free to use our Food Coding Guide (attached)  as a resource when navigating different dates. 

I will follow up with you as soon as I get updates regarding the products you asked about. 
[^Date Coding Guide.pdf]

Charity"", ""comment4"": ""06/26/2024 04:51;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Hi Andrea,

I hope you are doing well. I wanted to talk to you about the ticket you submitted. I apologize for the delay. One of my team members brought up your concerns regarding some items you received from us. After discussing your concerns about the salad dressing with my management and the Food Sourcing Team responsible for all the food that comes into the Food Bank, here are some points I wanted to share with you.

Regarding the salad dressing, our Food Resourcing Team does not have a specific recommendation for shelf-stable milk or salad dressing in our Food Coding Guide. We suggest following the USDA's recommendation regarding this product specifically and apologize for not being able to provide further insight. Partners and clients should use their eyes, noses, and, taste buds to determine if a food is spoiled and therefore unsafe to eat. Of course, if a product is showing any signs of spoilage such as rot, mold, foul odor, etc., we will accept a return. I have brought this issue to management's attention, and I agree that our Food Coding Guide needs improvement. I will raise this with our leadership for further review.

In response to your second point, I acknowledge the importance of best-by dates for our partners and their clients. However, our team faces challenges in obtaining these dates for donated products. One challenge arises during packing events when volunteers check and pack donated items into cases labeled as assorted on the menu. These assorted cases contain items from various donors and are packed without specific best-by date information for each individual product. Another challenge occurs when we receive donated products in different case lots-with different dates, making it difficult to provide accurate best-by dates to our partners. We don't know what case lot your order is going to be pulled from until its pulled the day before or two before its delivered or picked up. Although we practice FIFO (first in, first out) inventory management, the dynamic nature of our inventory makes it challenging to predict best-by dates with certainty. As our inventory of donated products increases, we are committed to improving our processes to provide partners with the information they need to make informed decisions. We are continuously seeking ways to improve our processes, and I encourage partners to participate in the upcoming  Partner meetings in July to address any questions or recommendations regarding product dates.

Thank you for bringing these concerns to our attention.

Warm regards,

""D""""}",,0.0

column1: This past Friday, we received 3 produce items that should not have been delivered especially the mustard greens. This is from SO180219.

The the mustard greens was already breaking down and gave off a terrible smell. Both the yellow summer squash and strawberry only 50% usable. The yellow squash looked like it was frozen and then defrosted with some molds. The strawberries were moldy. Both items did not look like they had significant issues from initial inspection. It is only when you start taking them out really looking carefully that you would notice the quality issues. I do not have pictures of the strawberries but I do have pictures of the mustard greens and the yellow summer squash. They are attached below.

i just saw that item 100757 was removed from our delivery tomorrow. It is a pallet of meals to go that we were going to offer our clients as back to school choice. We were planning giving at least 2-3 per family. Right now we are going to end up giving 1 per family. It is disappointing. I dropped the other individual cases and decided on a pallet thinking that surely CAFB knows how many full pallets they have of an item since it is large and there are only 15 posted (at least when I initially saw it). It is even more disappointing because every week it seems as though an item is being removed from our order. This week it is a full pallet of meals to go. Last week it was 6 cases of eggs, and 3 weeks ago a bin or corn.

I thought that when the number of items get posted to Partner Link, these are the number of items available to order. I am trying to understand why the items are missing by the time items get pulled. And it should not be happening almost every week. I have the same pallet ordered for delivery date 8/23. Am I going to assume that item is also gone since the same item is now not available or missing?
We appreciate what you all do but there is always room for improvement.

CiArra"", ""comment2"": ""10/09/2024 11:21;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Andrea,

I hope you are doing well. I wanted to write to you regarding the missing items list. I have been in communication with our Operations Department about the issue with your order. After searching the warehouse and conducting some internal inventory recalculations, we have identified inventory errors and mispicking for this order. A few weeks ago, we communicated to all our agency partners about the challenges we have been facing with inventory and operations. We acknowledge the impact this has on our partners and their distributions. We are working internally to address this issue by conducting more inventory calibration and providing additional training for our staff to improve accuracy in our Operations Department. Unfortunately, these items cannot be redelivered as we no longer have them. I understand this is frustrating and have reported this incident, as well as others from our partners, to my leadership. We are dedicated to improving your experience with us and want to ensure you have a better experience. Please accept our apology.

Sincerely,
Andrea

https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/service-desk/powered-by?utm_medium=jira-in-product&utm_source=jira_service_desk_email_footer&utm_content=capitalareafoodbank]{color:#707070}{color} 
 Sent on October 28, 2024 12:13:13 PM EDT  !https://linkprotect.cudasvc.com/url?a=https%3a%2f%2f80wmmks5.r.us-west-2.awstrack.me%2fI0%2f01010192d3e72441-8673f28f-1ea8-4b7d-b44f-c2f9db978825-000000%2fArTezVAI3CKOukZm_vs8yyLgeJk%3d398&c=E,1,iqN_AUyEDWO29_NWoIEDOreJJtaJb7R75XJcJD6jSE6ndkA6rLH-IdSPPpM9Thgox14WpsG-aZ9SoZTMmkar_51taRkc8xGpTHWuTkQn&typo=1!    {quote}"", ""comment3"": ""10/28/2024 01:30;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Hi Andrea, 

I spoke to the Regional Coordinators and below is the itnel that they had to share about this topic: 

_Partners cannot require clients to volunteer in exchange for food. This policy must be clearly communicated between both parties (partner site and volunteer). However, if a volunteer needs food and wishes to continue volunteering, partners have the option to take them on as clients as well. Since you are using Service Insights, the partners will need to create a client profile for the volunteer in the same manner as they do for all clients._ 

_Volunteers have the same access to food as clients. Therefore, if the partner has zip code or income restrictions, the volunteer must meet the same qualifications as clients do._

Let me know if you need any further questions! 

""D"" "", ""comment4"": ""10/28/2024 01:42;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:bdf05ada-890a-4498-8260-43dcc5ca4eea;Hi ""D"",

Thank you very much for the information. Our volunteers in need do have access to food but my coordinator was talking to another coordinator from the Maryland food bank and it was suggested that we need to find out CAFB's guidelines on CAFB food and volunteers. 

Thank you for the clarification. 

Sincerely,
Andrea

column1: This past Friday the delivery driver told one of our Pastors that he can't wait until 10 am and the pastor had to receive the order. The pastor said he went ahead and received the order because of what the driver told him but was concerned that our full order may not be there because he is unfamiliar with the receiving process. Our delivery window is 10 am-12 pm. I spoke with the driver around 9:30 and I told I will be there a little before 10 but he was gone by the time I arrived.

column1: Re: Important Update Regarding Your Orders ,PART1-8188,78752,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,eHnssreitKise ,e sseHKtineirs,2025-01-07 01:58:00,2025-01-11 01:30:00,,2025-01-07 04:29:00,,"Hello - I would like to reschedule the Jan. 8 delivery to the following Wednesday, Jan. 15. Either the 8-10 am or the 10-12pm delivery window is acceptable.
Please confirm so I can have the volunteers on hand.

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to address the challenges posed by the inclement weather we have experienced over the past couple of days. Unfortunately, this has left us two days behind in our pulling schedule, which has led us to make the difficult decision to cancel the orders originally scheduled for Wednesday, January 8th.

We sincerely regret any inconvenience this may cause to your distribution plans. We understand how vital these deliveries are to your operations.  *We encourage you to respond to this email and let us know whether you would like to finalize the cancellation of your order or reschedule it.*  Please note that we will need a response from your agency by the end of the business day ( *5 pm*) on  *January 7th*, or the order will be canceled on our end.

Please note that we are rescheduling orders, with the earliest openings being mid-week next week. This is due to our delivery and pickup schedules being full before the snow we experienced this week. Please reach out to us to coordinate further!

We are fully aware of the impact that inclement weather can have on our collective efforts, and we remain committed to ensuring the safety of our staff and yours during this time. Thank you for your understanding and support as we navigate this situation together. We are working quickly to get back on schedule.

Customer Relations{quote}",G. C.,Partner Knowledge/Training,,DC,,,Agency Administration -> Partner Trainings,Provide Operations/Transportation Feedback,English,Explanation Provided,0.0,,Email to Jira,10440,15:54:00,service-request,Done,2024-09-30 04:08:00,00:08:03.600000,{""comment1"": ""09/30/2024 04:08;712020:38c82492-84fe-40dc-8901-61d65a68f6d3;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.



Screenshots have been included to provide visual guidance (They are examples not for your agency). 

If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours

Unavailability of Fruit & Vegetables in Cases ,PART1-8152,78698,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,MNBTLTRN YAOEAR,OBTTEYNA NAMLRR,2025-01-04 01:01:00,2025-01-11 01:30:00,,2025-01-07 05:39:00,,"Hi Partner Support,

We were told that cases of fresh vegetables would be available some time ago. They are never available when we're placing our orders. So, does that mean they are really never going to be available anymore for small sites with no dock availabilty?
We have not been able to pick up fresh vegetables since Covid began and in-house shopping was discontinued.
Your positive response would be appreciated.

MaryAnn Tolbert",G. New H. B. C.,Request of Customer Relations,,DC,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Orders - Pre delivery -> Produce Request,Email Request,English,Question Answered,0.0,,Email to Jira,-300.0,00:00:00,service-request,Done,2025-01-07 05:39:00,00:14:53.700000,"{""comment1"": ""01/06/2025 08:14;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Relations. I appreciate your inquiry. We offer a variety of fruits and vegetables on our menu throughout the week, but the selection can vary depending on seasonal availability. During the winter months, for example, we typically have fewer options compared to the summer when a wider variety of produce is available. 

In recent weeks, the fruits and vegetables available have primarily included potatoes, apples, and carrots. Due to producelimitations placed on agencies, our Food Resources Team is working to bring in more produce items in case lot instead of large bins and full pallets, but this remains an ongoing challenge. Currently, all produce items must be ordered through PartnerLink, as there are no plans to reopen the agency mart for direct pickups.

I have two suggestions to enhance your experience in this situation. First, you can place orders up to 10 days in advance of your scheduled pickup and delivery date. I recommend placing your order as soon as the calendar opens and frequently checking PartnerLink for available produce. You can edit and add to your order until it locks for fulfillment, which is three business days prior to the shipment date. This flexibility allows you to include any additional items you may find during that 10-day window.

Another option is to explore our TEFAP program, a government-subsidized initiative through which participating partners can access additional items to supplement their regular orders. Please note that this program has specific requirements and is managed by the TEFAP team. For more information, you can reach out to Zaynab, the DC TEFAP coordinator: [zkadhem@capitalareafoodbank.org

column1: This is a RECURRING problem.  I place an order via INVOICE - not credit card.  However, when I want to edit the pending order the "Edit" button is greyed out. I place orders via INVOICE - not via credit card.  However, when I go to edit a pending order, the EDIT button is greyed out with a notation about editing not possible with credit card orders.  The order information shows it was placed via INVOICE.

I donâ€™t know if this is an issue only for our organization.  Alanna had offered that perhaps the problem is caused by the credit card listed in the database for us (although not used for the order).
It is very helpful to review the menu while an order is pending to be able to add any needed items that were not on the menu at the time of placing the order.
I request attention to this problem so that we may again have the ability to edit our pending orders as needed.
Your assistance on this matter is greatly appreciated!

I hope you're doing well. Thank you for getting in touch about the Virginia Menu. We've been informed by our Virginia partners about the urgent need for staple food pantry items, and we're actively working with your Regional Team and the Food Resourcing Team to restock and maintain these essential items on the menu.

We're planning to send out a detailed communication about this matter later this week. In the meantime, our Food Resources Team has shared that the following items are expected to be restocked in the warehouse by mid-September/early October, taking into consideration truck schedules and receiving scheduling:

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Milk, 1%, 8 ounces

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Spaghetti Sauce

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Lentils

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Corn Flakes

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Crisped Rice Cereal

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Toasted Oâ€™s

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Elbow Macaroni

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Elbow Macaroni, WW

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Instant coffee

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Green Tea

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Jelly: Strawberry and Grape

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  Pancake Syrup

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â  White, rice

Additionally, I spoke to the Food Resources Team about Mac and Cheese today, and they said that they are working on transferring it from the DC warehouse to the Virginia warehouse this week, so you will see it restocked in the next week or so. 

We truly value your feedback and want to reassure Virginia partners that we are committed to addressing this issue. Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

Take care,

You should be able to login to the new system using the following instructions: 

Partner Link 2.0 â€“ Password Reset
â€Š
The NEW Partner Link is now available! To gain access to the new site, you must first reset your password. Below are the steps to reset your password.
â€Š

# Go to the Partner Link log in page: [https://order.capitalareafoodbank.org/
column2:
https://order.capitalareafoodbank.org/]
# On the log in page, click on the link Forgot Password 
# On the next screen, enter in your email address. IMPORTANT: This must be the same email address that you use to log into the old Partner Link. 
# Within a few minutes, you will receive an email at the email address you typed in. NOTE: If you do not receive the email, please check your Spam and/or Trash folders.
# From the email, click on the Change Password button: 
# This will direct you to a page where you will set your new password 
# Type in your new password and then confirm the same password. Click on the Change Password button. If you get this error, then you didnâ€™t type the passwords exactly the same (remember, passwords are case-sensitive) 
# If both passwords match, after you click Change Password, you will be redirected back to the Log In page.
# Input your email address and your NEW password to gain access to the new Partner Link 2.0 site
â€Š
If you have any issues in this process, please contact [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
column3:
mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]

If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use.
Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on  {color:#e03e2d}*September 19th from 9 am to 10 am*{color}{color:#e03e2d}.{color} These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to [register
column2: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u]your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations.

column1: While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.

The Customer Relations Team {quote}",H. The system was trying to use the last of your 1-H Grant to cover the line for your peaches (#300387), but your 1-H Grant only had $316.14 left on it, which left a balance of *$505.46* and the same with the line with your macaroni and cheese (#300015), the system is trying to use the last of what was on your 1-G which was $141.07 but the line item had a total of $385.60 leaving a balance of *$244.53*. 

 However, if you would like to use your other grant, Grant 1-I, which has a larger balance and can cover the entire line item costs we can arrange that for you so that you won't have any remaining balance to pay for this sales order.

I hope you are doing well. Thank you for your question. Yes, our Food Resources team, which is responsible for procuring food, including produce items at the Food Bank, was very much involved in the conversation and collaboration regarding the produce limits. One of their initiatives is to start procuring cases for our smaller agencies that have produce limits under 2,000 lbs.

I also want to remind you that if you see a pallet of, for example, 2,000 lbs, the system will allow you to order over your limit. Customer Service will then reach out to you to discuss your options. If that is the only item available at that time and no cases are offered, we will permit the overage as long as it is not excessive.

Best,

column1: Fw: Quick Question ,PART1-8034,75732,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,n gnniKaaAl,lAagan niKn,2024-12-12 11:01:00,2024-12-19 01:30:00,,2024-12-12 02:31:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hi Team,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Would any of you all be able to provide some more context here around the recall policy / how we handle recalls in terms of client outreach?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} Let me know or if there is another person who may be able to help here!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
Ah, that is good to know! Would someone from your team be able to do a call to further explain your process? It may be a good model for us!
*{color:#666666} *Follow the Inova Healthy Plate Club on*{color} [{color:#666666} {color}{color:#0563C1} *Facebook*{color} {color:#666666} {color}

*{color:#004B8D} ****ATTENTION:*{color}**{color:#172B4D} *This email originated from outside of Inova. Please proceed with caution if asked to click links or open attachments.**{color}*{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}Yes, we do notify clients! It is up to the site to notify the clients, so for the DDP sites, those organizations along with our team will reach out to the who received food. For our agency partners, like you all who order from the menu, they are responsible for contacting the individuals.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

Thank you! For any of your direct distribution programs, like the family markets, do you do any notifications to individuals who received a product that was part of a recall? Thatâ€™s one thing we are trying to determine as part of our process â€“ if we should notify patients.
*{color:#666666} *Follow the Inova Healthy Plate Club on*{color} [{color:#666666} {color}{color:#0563C1} *Facebook*{color} {color:#666666} {color}
*{color:#004B8D} ****ATTENTION:*{color}**{color:#172B4D} *This email originated from outside of Inova. Please proceed with caution if asked to click links or open attachments.**{color}*

{color:#172B4D}Thank you for reaching out about this! While the Good Samaritan Law does protect food pantries and food banks from civil liability, we do still monitor the FDA recall announcements to ensure the safety of our clients. Please see CAFB's recall policy below. In addition to this, I am not sure of other healthcare providers who may have a policy in place for this. Gillian may be able to provide support there!{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}Let me know if I can help with anything else!{color}

{color:#172B4D}A food recall, as defined by the FDA, involves removing foods from the market that violate the regulations set by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration. Foods are recalled for various reasons, primarily due to contamination or failure to disclose essential allergens on the product label. It's important for food suppliers and distributors to stay informed about recalls, as consuming recalled foods may lead to illness or injury. If a product is recalled, the details will be specific to the item reflecting the brand, product name, freeze-by date, and other relevant information pertaining to that specific product. Items that do not match the description provided in the recall notice are not affected and can be safely consumed. In the event of a recall, it is recommended to return the product to the place of purchase or dispose of it to prevent consumption.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}The Capital Area Food Bank constantly monitors FDA food recall notifications and maintains regular contact with vendors and suppliers. In the event that we are made aware of a recalled inventory item, we will take immediate steps to remove it from all upcoming orders and notify our partners who may have received the item since it was added to our menu. Our Customer Service Team will use various communication channels to promptly inform all partners about the recall and the necessary steps to take with the product.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}If you have received an item from Capital Area Food Bank that you suspect has caused illness, please contact Customer Relations immediately. Provide your contact information, the date and time of the distribution where the food was distributed to clients, a description of the issue with the product, the item number/name, the date you received the product from our warehouse, and any illness or injury resulting from consuming the item. The Customer Relations Team will handle your complaint seriously and alert the relevant teams at Capital Area Food Bank to address the issue promptly.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}If you have any questions about this process, please contact{color} [{color:#172B4D}partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org{color}

We are creating an internal process for handling food recalls for our food programs. To inform this process, Iâ€™m hoping to learn from others doing this work. Do you know any healthcare systems/providers that have on-site pantries, and if so, can you connect me?

Also, from what I understand food banks/pantries donâ€™t do any notifications for recalls due to the Good Samaritan law. However, I want to make sure Iâ€™m correct â€“ does CAFB do anything for recalls, i.e. notifying pantries who received affected food?
*{color:#666666} *Follow the Inova Healthy Plate Club on*{color}*{color:#172B4D}{color} [{color:#172B4D} {color}{color:#0563C1} *Facebook*{color} {color:#172B4D} {color}

Good afternoon, Alanna,

I'm having trouble with the system; it will not allow me to forward this ticket to Jessica or respond directly to the partner. Could you please forward the response below on my behalf? Thank you!

----

Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. You had a great question about our recall process. 

For our DDP programs (mobile and community markets), the recall outreach process differs from that of the partnership teams. When a recall is identified, our Food Resources, Analytics, and Operations Teams collaborate with our programs and my team (Customer Relations) to contact the partners who ordered the affected items. It is then the partners' responsibility to reach out to their clients.

For DDP, the process is slightly different. I recommend contacting Jessica Arias, one of our managers on the DDP team, to learn more about how they notify their sites and assist those sites in informing their respective clients. 

Here is her contact information:

Jessica Arias  
[jarias@capitalareafoodbank.org

RE: Produce Boxes Damaged and Expired Food ,PART1-7502,69646,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,dad@rlgdretaaacamrcpoio.oisoifoepnpbrratrnknatoh,rralcmgpp.darpinosoroataineonadkhfdo@btcirratoea,2024-09-27 02:10:00,2024-10-05 01:31:00,,2024-10-01 08:10:00,,"Good afternoon,

Thank you sharing your concerns with your last order as well as photos. I have included Partner Support in this response, and they will work with the internal CAFB departments to convey the feedback and help you mitigate the issue.
Please use their email for any future order issues as well.
*Subject:* Produce Boxes Damaged and Expired Food

{color:#172B4D}I am just contacting you as we received two shipments yesterday and today. Both shipments have been damaged in one way or another. The boxes of fresh produce came very damaged towards the bottom and some of the items inside had to be thrown out due to being squished. Today we received expired peanut butter and will be unable to give that to our clients. I have attached photos of both things.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D}Please let me know what we can do about this situation{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

CR"", ""comment13"": ""10/01/2024 08:08;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for your message to our team and for your patience while we look into this matter.

I apologize for the issues with your two orders. Regarding the Produce Boxes, we have contacted your Regional Coordinators, Grace and Augusta, and they will communicate with Coastalâ€™s Customer Service Team to address the problem with your produce boxes that were not distributable. Augusta has offered to follow up with them and relay any next steps back to you.

As for the peanut butter, thank you for providing photos. We appreciate it. The peanut butter in your order, as well as many of our other donated items, have passed their ""best by"" date. This date indicates when the product will be at its best flavor or quality and is not a safety date. Itâ€™s a quality date that encourages consumers to eat food while it is in its prime state. Food that is past this date is not bad and should not be thrown away. We provide a food coding guide to our partners that explains these dates further. We want to reassure you that the peanut butter is not expired and will not cause any harm to consumers. We offer the Food Coding Guides as a resource and we have them printed and available to order for partners as well to pass out at distributions. 

[^Food Coding Guidance.pdf]

Thank you,

There is a balance of $18.01 in Grant FY24 Region MOCO 1-H and another balance of $6380.86 on Grant FY24 Region MOCO 1-I. Thank you.,I. of W.,Partner Knowledge/Training,SO158182,MD,ERP,,Billing / Grants -> Grant Support,Billing Support,English,Issue Resolved (ERP/Accounting),5.0,2024-04-29 03:40:00,Portal,8880,05:48:00,service-request,Done,2024-04-29 01:10:00,00:57:04.100000,"{""comment1"": ""04/25/2024 04:57;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for contacting our Customer Service. I'd be happy to assist you with your query.

Our system applies grants on a per-line-item basis, which means that only one grant can be applied to each line item. In the case of your order, the line item is $817.00, and the system initially used the last of your FY24 MD Region Moco 1-G grant, which was $75.59. 

However, as per your request, I have contacted our IT department to apply your FY24 MD Region MOCO 1-I grant to that line item since it is the only grant you have that can cover the entire amount.

Please note that moving forward, the $75.59 remaining on your 1-G grant and the $18.01 left on your 1-H grant may not cover the entire line item cost. If this happens, it is because our system applies the grants on a per-line-item basis. If you have a line item that costs less than these amounts in future orders, then you will have no remaining balance.

I hope this clarifies the situation. If you have any more questions, please feel free to ask.

Best regards,

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

If you still need assistance please attend one of our online Office Hours every Wednesday from 10am-10am: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours

column1: Re: Rescheduling your order ,PART1-8176,78738,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,hraee lzrbGHbiegaei,ebbeaHirlehzeGir ag,2025-01-07 12:12:00,2025-01-11 01:30:00,,2025-01-07 02:57:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Good afternoon,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I would like to schedule my delivery for Friday, January 10th, 8:00 am - 10:00 am{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I hope this email finds you well. Due to the inclement weather and the resulting closure of our operations today, we are unable to process orders as scheduled.

We kindly ask if you would like to reschedule your order for some time next week to please respond to this email. Please contact us at your earliest convenience to let us know your preferred date and time for rescheduling or if you would prefer us to cancel your order.{color}

{color:#172B4D} We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding and cooperation. If you have any questions or need further assistance, please do not hesitate to reach out. Thank you for your attention to this matter, and we look forward to hearing from you soon.{color}

Thank you,
Customer Relations
Capital Area Food Bank"", ""comment2"": ""04/29/2024 11:36;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning,

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to inform you that you can only apply one grant for a single line item. The system was trying to use the last of your 1-G to cover the line for your corn meal (#300572), but your 1-G Grant only had $10.38 left on it, which left a balance of *$381.77*.

However, if you would like to use your other grant, Grant 1-I or Grant 1-H, which have a larger balances and can cover the entire line item cost we can arrange that for you so that you won't have any remaining balance to pay for this sales order.

Please let me know which grant you would like to use, and I will put in a ticket with my IT team to make the necessary changes.

Thank you,

""D"""", ""comment3"": ""04/29/2024 01:54;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:8a44ba33-75eb-4823-bfab-6a81dc3abfee;Yes you can use anyone of our grant funds to cover"", ""comment4"": ""04/29/2024 02:04;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Okay, I will have our IT team go ahead and make this change. Can you confirm that you will not be editing this order any further? If you edit the order after this change is made, it will revert back to its original state. If you do plan on editing it, that is fine-we will make the change closer to the delivery date. "", ""comment5"": ""04/29/2024 02:15;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:8a44ba33-75eb-4823-bfab-6a81dc3abfee;No, I will not."", ""comment6"": ""04/29/2024 08:47;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good evening,

Your order has been updated and your grant has been applied accordingly. You have no balance due for this sales order. 

""D"" ""}",,0.0

I am very sorry to hear that this happened. Our system is supposed to hold items in your cart for 24 hours so this should not be happening. However, sometimes this does happen if many partners are ordering an item at the same time, which is the case with popular items like vegetable oil and produce. 

Yes, it would likely help if you placed your order as soon as possible after starting the order. This officially commits the item to your order. 

If you have any additional questions or concerns, please donâ€™t hesitate to reach out. 

Best,

mailto:jira@capitalareafoodbank.atlassian.net]"", ""comment3"": ""03/08/2023 10:25;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Hi Marian, 

I reached out to our food resourcing team, and they said they were made aware of this by other partners. Our team has reached out to Feeding America to see if they could provide assistance on obtain a recipe for this item. My colleague said she would get back to me, as soon as she heard back from them. 

Our apologies about this. 

DH "", ""comment4"": ""03/14/2023 03:55;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Hi Marian, 

I am so sorry for the delay. Feeding America got back to our food resourcing team about the biscuits. Please see below: 

*_Rolled Biscuits: Yield 6-8 biscuits. 1 pkg Jack & the Beanstalk Buttermilk Biscuit Mix, 1/2 cup water, preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Blend biscuit mix and water to a soft dough. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, knead several times. Pat or roll dough 1/2 inch thick. Cut with 2 inch floured cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 10 minutes. Drop Biscuits: Follow recipe above except do not knead. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes._*

*_Do not eat raw batter, dough or mix. Corn Muffins: Yield 6 - 8 muffins depending on size. 1 pkg. Jack & the Beanstalk Cornbread Mix and Corn muffin mix. 1 egg. 1/3 cup milk. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Grease muffin pan or use paper baking cups. Blend ingredients. Batter will be slightly lumpy. (for maximum crown on muffins let batter rest for 3 or 4 minutes, stir lightly before filling cups.) Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 15 - 20 minutes or until golden brown._*

Â Thank you for your patience.

Unfortunately, our system does not have the capability to transfer an item between orders. You can only remove the item from one order and then add that item to the other order but of course there is no guarantee that someone else might not take that available inventory. 

Additionally, partners do not have the capability to edit the date of their order. You can send a request to partner support for your order date be to be updated, but we can only do so if there are available appointments and the new order date is more than 3 days in advance of the ship date. 

Hope this information helps! 

Best,

Why have there been no new items (including produce) added to the shopping menu in almost 2 weeks? ,PART1-6881,61560,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,o9l4momnhmsji@.c6ag3,9ghm6om.c4nios3j@lma,2024-07-03 09:35:00,2024-07-09 01:30:00,,2024-07-03 11:17:00,,,K.,Partner Knowledge/Training,,VA,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Feedback - Concern / Negative -> Menu,General Questions,English,Feedback Communicated,0.0,,Email to Jira,10740,14:17:00,service-request,Done,2024-07-03 11:17:00,00:35:28.900000,"{""comment1"": ""07/03/2024 09:35;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;Hi mjohns6439@gmail.com, 

We just received your request for assistance. We will reply as soon as possible.

Thank you,
Customer Relations
Capital Area Food Bank"", ""comment2"": ""07/03/2024 11:10;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning,

Thank you for your questions about the limited items on the menu. While I don't have a general answer, there are several factors at play. Firstly, at certain times of the year, we have constraints on our receiving calendar, which leads to fewer inventory trucks due to scheduling conflicts. Currently, we are facing this situation as we were closed for Juneteenth, went through our bi-annual inventory last week, and will also be closed for the July 4th observance next week. Additionally, as we prepare for our move back to home building in the Virginia region, there may be a slight shift in the amount of products as we transition inventory from one location to another. This means we have been and will continue to receive fewer trucks than usual and are trying to schedule loads that fit within this restricted schedule.

Moreover, while donations vary, we are actively working to increase the amount of donated food we receive and make it available through our Partner Direct Program and the menu. This issue will be discussed in an upcoming in-person partner meeting in July, giving partners the opportunity to hear from our leadership and our Food Resourcing Team, who are responsible for sourcing all the food on the menu, both donated and purchased.

Let me know if you have any further questions or concerns.

Thanks,

""D""""}",,0.0

Re: Change in Your Upcoming Sales Order ,PART1-7932,74498,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,oteeu.tssmenant@s.isv-etmcyi,-is.tesmaoene@ci.nstusttmvye,2024-11-25 08:49:00,2024-11-30 01:30:00,,2024-11-26 08:19:00,,"What was the ordering error? If I did something wrong, Iâ€™d like to know so I donâ€™t repeat it.
{quote}On Nov 25, 2024, at 8:04 PM, partner Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) <system@sent-via.netsuite.com> wrote:

We regret to inform you that we had to remove or reduce the quantity of item(s) from your order  *SO183847*. Below is a list of item(s) and reason for the change. We understand that this change may cause inconvenience to you and your distribution plans, and we apologize for the inconvenience. Please note that if you are receiving this notification after your order has been locked, which is three business days before your order is due to be picked up or delivered, this change is most likely occurring during or after the pulling stage and unfortunately, we cannot replace the item removed or make any further additions during this time period.

To review an updated version of your order, please log in to PartnerLink and visit the Order History tab. If you have any queries or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
Thank you for your understanding and continued support.

Partner Support {quote}",K. F. Inc,Request of Customer Relations,,,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Orders - Pre delivery -> General Questions,Email Request,English,Question Answered,0.0,,Email to Jira,10800,16:00:00,service-request,Done,2024-11-26 08:19:00,00:14:35.900000,"{""comment1"": ""11/26/2024 08:14;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning,

Thank you for reaching out to us about this! You did not do anything wrong. An ""order issue"" means that we ordered this product from a farmer or vendor, and something went wrong with our order. For example, they may have been scheduled to deliver it one week but informed us they couldn't come until the following week, or they told us we were supposed to receive 10 cases but only delivered 6.

Rest assured, this is not your fault!

Best,  
""D""""}",,0.0

Thank you for reaching out. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

Jon"", ""comment9"": ""10/10/2024 03:36;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;I have updated your account and clicked on the verify button. The hours listed are not the general hours of operation for your office or establishment, but instead indicate the days and hours when you distribute food. Your agency is listed as distributing food on Thursdays from 3pm to 5pm. You will be asked to confirm this information approximately once every quarter (or every 3 months). We will require you to log in and confirm that you are distributing food at the same time. To do so, please log into your account, go to the ""hours of operation"" tab, and click on 'verify' if the information is correct and unchanged. You can then proceed with your shopping. If you need to change your distribution hours, you should use the 'edit' button. This information is shared with the broader community, so it's important that our distribution hours are accurate. Thank you! column1: SO194429 - Mice Incident Report ,PART1-8623,82808,[System] Service request,Completed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,nen.olibngomdeddirn@aunyafjto,udtylaegnjnnedrnbafo.oindimo@,2025-02-20 06:28:00,2025-02-26 04:37:00,,2025-02-25 06:58:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Dear Partner Support,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Last Friday, 2/14/25, sale order SO194429 was delivered to our location. It included 3 bins of cereal, item 100862. At first sight, we noticed rodent droppings on top of cereal boxes in one of those bins. That bin was not accepted and the delivery driver loaded it back up inside his truck.{color}

{color:#172B4D}The other two bins were b{color} {color:#b36ae2}*r*{color}{color:#172B4D}ought upstairs to our storage room. To our surprise, a few minutes later, we saw a mouse coming out of one bin and returning inside that bin.{color}

{color:#172B4D} We had to act quickly since other food items were stored inside this room. We immediately wrapped both bins, loaded them inside our vehicle and drove to two landfill sites to dispatch the two open bins with donated assorted cereal. Upon dispatching them, our staff saw two mice. This confirmed our fear that more than one mouse had entered inside our building and our storage room through the open bin cereals that we ordered.{color}

{color:#172B4D} Of course, the issue was not over and the following Monday, 2/17/25, we caught another mouse. We will continue to closely monitor our storage room and other areas to be certain that the problem has been eradicated. Attached are pictures of what was left behind after we removed the two bins out of the storage room.{color}

{color:#172B4D} This experience was very disturbing, and a solution needs to be implemented quickly. This put us behind schedule by four days due to the intervention that we put in place. We also had to throw away our products that the mice had contaminated.{color}

{color:#172B4D} CAFB has been such a great partner to us and we are forever grateful for the 'all in' support that you have been providing us to allow us to help our underserved communities. That is why we are sharing this information and our experience to you so this can be further looked at and hopefully avoided. We are in this together to strengthen food security, so we know this kind of issue will be attended to and taken seriously by both parties.{color}
{color:#172B4D} We look forward to your feedback or resolution around this matter.{color}

 I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to reach out personally to follow up on the recent incident and to express my sincere apologies for any disruption it may have caused you.  I have escalated this matter to our Operations Director, and I want you to know that we have a new leader in Operations who is dedicated to ensuring we serve our partners with the utmost care and precision. She is committed to making improvements and has assured me that we are taking significant steps to prevent such situations from occurring in the future.   Some of the measures weâ€™re implementing include:  1. Continuing our routine pest control efforts. 2. Collaborating with our pest control company, which visited our facility on Monday to conduct additional work beyond our normal maintenance. 3. Strengthening our inspection processes to ensure that all pullers, drivers, and inspectors thoroughly check every order once it's staged. 4. Focusing on the quality of products going out to our partners. 5. Preparing for the warmer months ahead to maintain a rodent-free and clean environment for the food we deliver.  I truly empathize with the impact this situation may have had on your operations, and I want to assure you that we are committed to providing a better service moving forward. Please know that we value your partnership and appreciate your understanding during this time.  As a gesture of goodwill, we would like to waive the delivery fees for both your recent order and your upcoming order on March 3rd.  If you have any questions or concerns, please donâ€™t hesitate to reach out. Your feedback is important to us, and weâ€™re here to help.  Thank you for your understanding.  

Warm regards,

column1: {color:#172B4D} Please move SO160977 from Monday 5/27/24 to Tuesday 5/28/24, 8am-10am.{color}

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused.

Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule.

In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding.
Thank you for your patience and cooperation.
{color:#4E8227}Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution{color}{color:#4E8227}{color}
