column1: Re: Change in Your Upcoming Sales Order ,PART1-8371,80411,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,ecietuis@nny..ovsmstatteesm-,eonsicmva.mtt@stistseu-.eyen,2025-01-26 08:34:00,2025-01-31 01:31:00,,2025-01-27 02:51:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Hello,{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I received this e-mail below on Friday evening, 1/24/25, that informed me of the removal of item 520059 from sale order SO191436.{color}
{color:#172B4D} However I found it again available to order, same quantity, on Sunday evening, 1/26/25. I added it again, same quantity, to my next order SO191941.{color}
{color:#172B4D} Could you please let me know why it was removed from my order?{color}
{color:#172B4D} Could you guarantee that the item is available and it won't be remove again from SO191941?{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
*Subject:* Change in Your Upcoming Sales Order{color}

We regret to inform you that we had to remove or reduce the quantity of item(s) from your order  *SO191436*. Below is a list of item(s) and reason for the change. We understand that this change may cause inconvenience to you and your distribution plans, and we apologize for the inconvenience. Please note that if you are receiving this notification after your order has been locked, which is three business days before your order is due to be picked up or delivered, this change is most likely occurring during or after the pulling stage and unfortunately, we cannot replace the item removed or make any further additions during this time period.

column1: I'm hoping you are well. I needed to make some changes to my order yesterday but unfortunately I forgot that Monday was a holiday and the order was already locked.
My request,(see below), was denied because the order was already fulfilled.
Would you please help me in that matter?
If it is impossible to reduce the amounts of some of the items, then can you remove the only frozen item, 520388 chicken leg quarters {color:#172B4D}, in order SO174321?{color}
I hope this message found you well. Would you please make the following changes to order SO174321.
I will create another order for 9/9/24 and add the items I removed if they are still available.

RE: Letting you all know about some contaminated fod ,PART1-7126,64916,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,mdnrh@ciaorroiaebkdnc.orpostoreptaitapaalfndgoar,oiinidfam@petsocrgottporaaobrkdaehlarrcr.ananodp,2024-08-07 09:29:00,2024-08-11 01:30:00,,2024-08-07 04:51:00,,"Good morning,

I am sorry to hear about the spoiled bags you received. I am looping in Partner Support who will coordinate with our inventory teams to let them know about the situation. They are available 9-5PM every week day to assist with ordering issues/challenges.
*Subject:* Letting you all know about some contaminated fod

We got a delivery from CAFB this week with various items. There were a few mice openings in our corn meal bags. We just wanted to let you all know and be aware. We were able to keep a majority of the bags, but had to get rid of a few. If there is someone else I should notify, please let me know.

RE: Edit order to add produce ,PART1-7374,68034,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,CH,ausF iutrAcgek,irtAugesFauc k,2024-09-10 10:50:00,2024-09-14 01:30:00,,2024-09-10 01:59:00,,"Good morning Pastor Samantha,
Thanks for reaching out, Iâ€™m so happy to hear everything is going well! I went into your Sales Order and added a bin of corn to ensure youâ€™d get some (produce tends to disappear quickly).

I am looping in our Partner Support team to answer your  *billing questions (in bold below*) â€“ theyâ€™re the experts on all things â€œSales Orderâ€ and I would recommend saving their information for future reference as well. I also attached a contact book for any other questions that might arise that are outside my prevue.

I hope this email finds you well. Things have been going really well for us the last few weeks for our pantry! We made a purchase last week in hopes to add on produce this week. However, this morning when I went to go add on produce *, I got the notice that I cannot edit the order if we paid with a credit card*.  *Could you let me know more about this issue and how we can proceed in the future? Can we only add produce to our order later if we get an invoice?*
We are really hoping to get that bin of corn if possible! Thanks!

A. for S. to H.,Request of Customer Relations,,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Orders - Pre delivery -> General Questions,Email Request,English,Question Answered,0.0,,Email to Jira,8940,09:37:00,service-request,Done,2024-11-05 03:22:00,00:44:13.600000,"{""comment1"": ""11/05/2024 10:44;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to us! I connected with our Operations Department regarding your concern. Unfortunately, we cannot unstack the bins of fruit. We recommend exploring options for equipment that could help manage the unstacking of the bins.

The reason we stack the bins on top of each other is to save space in the truck, allowing us to load your entire order efficiently. There are limitations to the capacity we can utilize in the truck.

At this time, we do not have any other options, but I will inform our Operations Team of your concerns so they can take them into consideration.

Thank you,

""D"""", ""comment2"": ""11/05/2024 11:12;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:5ebf50a5-88dc-407f-bd87-560084808b1f;Ok, thank you for getting back to me."", ""comment3"": ""11/05/2024 03:22;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;No problem! ""}",,0.0

"", ""comment3"": ""01/08/2025 01:49;712020:b15fa988-bc60-49b4-aa6f-e30b7a3629c1;Good afternoon,

Thank you for contacting Customer Support. I have registered this Letter of Authorization for your agency. Our mandatory SMART Shopping Training is the last step new shoppers need to gain access to Partnerlink and begin submitting orders for your agency. These virtual sessions are an hour long and are held twice a month for each region. Please note that you only have to attend one training to gain access to become an authorized shopper. 

The next SMART Shopping Training will be held on: *1/23/2024* from 10-11am

To register for any and all trainings, please use this link: Virginia: [https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/smart-shopping-training-va-

CiArra"", ""comment2"": ""09/24/2024 02:33;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation.[^Updating Hours of Operations (Partner Facing Document).pdf] 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

B.,Partner Knowledge/Training,,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Agency Administration -> Update Information,General Questions,English,Information Updated (NetSuite),0.0,,Email to Jira,10800,16:00:00,service-request,Done,2024-09-26 08:45:00,00:40:29.700000,"{""comment1"": ""09/25/2024 06:40;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Thank you for your inquiry on our Hours of Operations Feature on PartnerLink. We encouraged all partners to attend one of the four trainings that we hosted between August and September to ensure that everyone was well-equipped to utilize this feature effectively. This feature is crucial for maintaining accurate information about your agency's operating hours, which in turn updates our [Get Help Map
column2: https://www.capitalareafoodbank.org/find-food-assistance/] on the website. The Get Help Map is a tool that clients use to locate nearby CAFB Partners, so it's essential to have the correct hours displayed. If you were unable to attend the trainings, don't worry. There are alternative options available, such as accessing the resource on PartnerLink under the Partner Resources tab, or signing up for [Customer Relations Office Hours
column3: https://capitalareafoodbank.zoom.us/zbook/partner-support/customer-relations-office-hours] held every Wednesday from 10am-11am. Please note that due to the nature of the training, there are no recordings or slides available, as it involved a live demo and Q&A session. While partners are not being reprimanded for not attending a training, it's important to highlight that starting *October 1st*, partners who have not updated or confirmed their hours will see a banner prompting them to do so before placing an order. You will need to take this action to proceed with making an order. If your hours have not changed, simply verify them by accessing the Agency Overview section after clicking your agency name on PartnerLink. If changes are necessary, please update them accordingly. For further assistance, please contact us at [partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org
column4:
mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]. "", ""comment2"": ""09/25/2024 08:16;712020:57080dd2-2594-4ec0-a18f-205666a1875e;So I went and clicked verify. Are we good now?

Thanks, Jeff"", ""comment3"": ""09/26/2024 08:44;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Yes, you are good. In the future, when you receive requests for updates, your account is not locked; it is simply asking for you to verify your information before you can proceed with placing an order.

Have a great day!

""D""""}",,0.0

column1: Re: Reminder for Mandatory Hours of Operations Training (One Training Remaining!) ,PART1-7433,68606,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,ty-tmnoeie.netsssuei@.cmtsva,cay-iststmnn..eseumvst@otiee,2024-09-16 11:54:00,2024-09-20 01:30:00,,2024-09-16 12:51:00,,"Someone needs to call me:

If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use.
Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on  {color:#e03e2d}*September 19th from 9 am to 10 am*{color}{color:#e03e2d}.{color} These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to [register
column2: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u]your agency. Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations.

column1: While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared, all partners are expected to attend the live (online) training to meet the requirement. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.

The Customer Relations Team {quote}",M. UMC,,,,,,,General Questions,English,,0.0,,Portal,9660,,service-request,Done,2024-03-25 11:26:00,00:23:22,"{""comment1"": ""03/25/2024 11:23;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning!

Thank you for your patience regarding this matter. I have read your email and I am truly sorry to hear that you did not receive your applesauce in your last order. Upon checking, I found that we currently do not have any more free applesauce available on the menu. We will have to wait until the item is restocked before it can be added another order of yours. 

In the meantime, I have rescheduled the delivery date of your SO153396, which includes the applesauce, to Wednesday the 27th. I had to keep the separate sales order for the applesauce because your produce order is on a different account (your push account). However, I have informed our Transportation Team to deliver both orders together and have waived the delivery fee for the applesauce.

Furthermore, I have contacted our Transportation Team to schedule an immediate pallet pick-up. If they are unable to send a driver today, I have requested that the driver who delivers your order on Wednesday has enough space to pick up any remaining pallets after delivering your food.

Once again, I apologize for the inconvenience.

""D"""", ""comment2"": ""03/25/2024 04:18;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:2b0cfede-13de-4a98-9419-5cbca5c09cc6;Thank you so very much ""D""!

Happy New Year! I hope you had a great holiday. I have attached our Inclement Weather Policy below.

[^Inclement Weather Policy.pdf]

In the event that it snows, we will wait for information from our leadership, including the Head of Operations, to determine if we will have a formal delay or closure - we do not follow the governmentâ€™s decisions regarding weather. For example, if we announce a 2-hour delay, all delivery and pickup windows will be pushed back accordingly. This means that if you had an 8 AM - 10 AM delivery, it will now be scheduled for 10 AM - 12 PM.

If we face a complete closure due to the weather, there will be no deliveries or pickups. On such days, the Customer Relations team will be available to reschedule deliveries and reach out to all partners regarding their orders.

Additionally, please keep in mind that depending on the amount of snow, there may be impacts on the days following the snowfall. If we do have a closure, we will do our best to accommodate our partners' schedules while ensuring that orders are not affected the following day.

I hope this helps! Please let me know if you need any further information.

Best,

I am happy to provide further insight. The pallet you ordered will not be removed from your order and will be delivered on the 21st.

Once partners are more familiar of this process, we will begin adjusting orders, in communication with you, to have your orders align closer to your monthly allotted poundage. 

You are able to continue submitting orders as your agency allows, but for the rest of this or any month, you will no longer be eligible to order more produce once the limit has been met or exceeded.

{color:#172B4D}{color}"", ""comment4"": ""07/03/2024 10:46;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Julia,

We primarily use the Food Coding Guide to help partners navigate such questions. When there are gaps, we recommend relying on research and information available online, particularly the USDA website. Furthermore, we advise partners and clients to use their senses (sight, smell, and taste) to determine if a food is spoiled and unsafe to eat.[Food Product Dating

On May 13, 2024, at 10:32â€¯AM, Joanna Miller <jmiller@capitalareafoodbank.org> wrote:
I am reaching out because VDACS has provided us with  *new TEFAP income guidelines*, to be used immediately. Please print the attached document and begin using it to determine client eligibility.

If you are using Link2Feed or Service Insights, it will take a few days for the new income guidelines to be updated within those systems. Please print a copy of the new guidelines and refer to them if the system tells you that a client is ineligible based on income. Itâ€™s possible that under the new guidelines, they actually are eligible. If that happens, go ahead and mark the person as eligible, even if the system is suggesting that they are not. This should not be an issue for too long.
Please let me know if you have any questions!

C.,Ops Issue,SO176178,VA,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Feedback - Concern / Negative -> Transportation,Email Request,English,Feedback Communicated,0.0,,Email to Jira,10200,08:00:00,service-request,Done,2024-10-01 08:22:00,00:13:11.800000,"{""comment1"": ""10/01/2024 10:13;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning Mitilde,

I hope you are doing well. Thank you for sharing your feedback with us; it is very valuable. I will follow up with the Transportation Leadership Team to address the way the drivers communicate with partners about this issue.

To provide some context, there are two main reasons why drivers may not take pallets when dropping off food during a delivery. Firstly, they may have food for an immediate order or need to pick up food from another site for the warehouse, which means they cannot have food and pallets on the truck at the same time due to food safety (Pallets are often leftoutside- on the ground, possibly in the rain, and are often dirty) and consideration for our partners. Secondly, our drivers may be on tight schedules and do not have the time for a pallet pickup due to their busy delivery schedules, especially during the busy season.

There is no reason why a driver could not explain this to you at the time, and I will ensure that this information is communicated to them. I apologize for your experience. 

Thank you,

column2: {color:#172B4D}We are thrilled to announce that on August 5th, we will be launching a new feature on PartnerLink. This feature will enable partners to update their Hours of Operations for your distributions. This new feature is very exciting because it means that you will be able to update your records whenever necessary. This ensures that we have the most up-to-date information in our internal systems and for clients to utilize. As a reminder, once approved, the information we gather from your updates will be linked to the information provided in our online tool that clients can use to locate food assistance: {color}[{color:#172B4D}Get Help Map.{color}

{color:#172B4D}To ensure that all partners understand how to utilize this function, we will host four training sessions: two in August and two in September. These sessions are designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and also provide an opportunity to talk to our team about PartnerLink and provide feedback. Please note that this training is  *+mandatory+*. You can use the links below to register your agency. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we welcome and encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We recommend that this person work closely with the food program and has a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared,  *all partners are expected to attend the live training to fulfill the requirements*. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.{color}

column3: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u]{color:#172B4D} to register. Upon selecting a training date and completing the form, you will receive the corresponding Zoom link via email.{color}

column2: {color:#172B4D}We are also excited to announce that the Customer Relations team will be hosting office hours every Wednesday in August and September from 10 am to 11 am starting August 14th. If you have any questions or support needs related to the new PartnerLink feature, this time is available to you.{color}

{color:#172B4D}Additionally, this opportunity will allow partners to interact with the Customer Relations Team, ask questions, and receive additional support regarding PartnerLink, menu items, new website features, and more. Please come prepared with questions and examples of issues that you may be experiencing with PartnerLink. Sharing your experiences is valuable, as it could help others facing similar issues. If you have specific recurring issues unique to your organization, we may need to take down your information and set up a one-on-one meeting to address them thoroughly and ensure the office hours are productive for all partners. Please note that if there are no attendees in the first 15 minutes of the office hours, we will cancel that week's session.{color}
{color:#172B4D}To register for Customer Relations office hours, please click{color}[{color:#172B4D} here.{color}
{color:#172B4D}We appreciate your ongoing partnership, collaboration, and look forward to seeing you at one of our training sessions or during our office hours.{color}

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. If the hours are not correct, please make the necessary changes by clicking â€œeditâ€, submit them, and once approved by your Regional Coordinator, the updated hours will be officially updated.

column1: Charging for Mixed TEFAP Orders ,PART1-8122,78491,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,LhaxAsi rel,AxeLs haril,2024-12-24 02:26:00,2025-01-29 01:30:00,,2025-01-24 12:34:00,2025-01-03 12:00:00,"Hi team,

I hope you are doing well! I recently learned that partners are being charged for orders that are mixed TEFAP and non-TEFAP. I double checked with the states, and no cost can be associated with TEFAP, even if there are other items included. Can you please remove the associated charge, and let me know if you have questions or concerns before moving forward.
Austin, just including you as an FYI.

Alexis",N. I.,,,All,,,Agency Administration,General Questions,English,Explanation Provided,0.0,,Portal,9300,15:31:00,service-request,Done,2025-01-24 12:34:00,00:20:15.900000,"{""comment1"": ""01/03/2025 01:20;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning, Alexis,

I hope this message finds you well, and Happy New Year! Thank you for providing this important information; it is definitely something we need to note.

To give you some background, partners have been charged delivery fees for orders that include a mix of TEFAP products and other donated or purchased items for some time. As stated in our SMART Shopping Policy, orders that contain only TEFAP products do not incur a delivery fee. However, orders that mix TEFAP with purchased or donated products do have a delivery fee associated with them.

I do not have the ability to remove delivery fees from all orders, as these fees are automatically added when partners place their orders. I believe we will need to submit an ERP ticket to stop this charge permanently, as it is an automated process. 

To clarify what the ticket would entail: Are we asking for no delivery fees to be applied to any orders containing any TEFAP items for al regions? Additionally, will we need to issue refunds for past orders that were charged delivery fees due to the mix of TEFAP and other products? I anticipate that partners will inquire about previous orders that included these fees as we proceed with this change and it also may be a good idea to plan for a formal communication to TEFAP partners since this is a change in poliy that we have previously stated to them. 

Is there a deadline for when this needs to be implemented? I understand that it should be done as soon as possible, but any changes/refunds to delivery fees are always approved by Austin, who is currently out until January 9th.

Thank you for bringing this matter back to our attention again, hope to resolve this as soon as possible! 

Best,  
""D"""", ""comment2"": ""01/03/2025 05:19;6064f0ca1613f30068073e90;Hey ""D"", happy new year and thanks for your response! Yes, weâ€™re asking for no delivery fees to be applied to any orders containing any TEFAP items for al regions. But, I donâ€™t think we need to issue refunds or change this immediately. I can flag this to Austin for when she returns and circle back to you. Agreed that weâ€™ll need to send out a communication, and my thought is we can word it as this will be our process going forward. "", ""comment3"": ""01/24/2025 12:33;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Closing this ticket as this issue is currently being handled by Alexis and Austin. If any further steps are taken, the associated teams will be made aware. ""}",,0.0

column1: Re: Corrective Action Plan - New Hope and Life Church of God ,PART1-7681,71917,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,aDedindaHr lue C.,d.eaa ie undlCDrH,2024-10-24 11:28:00,2024-10-30 01:30:00,,2024-10-24 02:57:00,,"Lucy, First, let me thank you and the TEFAP program for allowing us to serve. We have been a part of the Capital Area Food Bank since 2009, that's 15 years of service. The volunteers that come to work with us do so at the kindness of their heart. Our Community is mult-cultural. People who are afraid of the impact of completing the form. At the Civil Rights meeting, I asked the question of how we can educate the community to help them understand that they wouldn't lose their benefits by completing the form. By saying, you can't have food unless you fill out the form is heartbreaking.

We are doing what we can, and to constantly be threatened of suspension is not a good feeling. I can't imagine any agency taking such steps over FOOD. These volunteers have worked tirelessly. If you need to come and get the foods we have, please feel free to do so. Let us know the date and time so that someone will be available. I spoke to Cynthia, and she informed me that  *NO TEFAP Food* was distributed in August. I will do the inventory, send you the forms we collected and that is all we can do.
On Thu, Oct 24, 2024 at 9:34â€¯AM Lucy Paredes <[lparedes@capitalareafoodbank.org

{color:#172B4D} I thought it would be best to answer on this email thread as you can more easily refer back to the Corrective Action Plan attached to the first email. I appreciate you sending along the pictures of the temperature logs and the civil rights training certificate. The Corrective Action Plan outlines 2 issues, the missing SDI forms and missing inventory reports.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D}The due date of 10/23/2024 was for the signed Corrective Action Plan to be emailed back to me along with a plan to prevent this issue from happening again in the future, please see the last bullet point below each issue, and lastly the missing inventory reports to be submitted. In your case, that is May and August of 2024. Like said in one of the emails below, if{color}{color:#172B4D} you submitted the missing months, you should have received an email with a PDF copy via email. If you could send me that, then it would clear up the missing inventory reports.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}

{color:#172B4D} Since I will be out of town tomorrow, Friday 10/25 and Monday 10/28, I will allow for one additional extension. The new date is Wednesday, October 30th, 2024. Please know that if these items are not submitted by end of day on October 30th, there will be a suspension placed on your TEFAP account. Any suspension that I do does not impact your ability to order regular CAFB food.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} To recap the final submission deadline for the signed CAP, summaries, and missing reports are due by End of Day, 5pm, on Wednesday October 30th.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color:#172B4D} I hope this clarifies any confusion.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}
{color}{color:#4e8227}4900 Puerto Rico Ave NE, Washington, DC 20017{color}{color:inherit}
{color:#172B4D}*From:* New Hope And Life Church of God <{color}[{color:#172B4D}newhopeandlifechurchofgod@gmail.com{color}
*Subject:* Re: Corrective Action Plan - New Hope and Life Church of God{color}

Good morning, Lucy, I plan to forward the certificate to you tomorrow. Also, the other person that was at the training, took the forms to make the certificates. We would not have been issued the certificate if we weren't there. There should be some accountability also on the facilitators part. I signed the form upon coming into the room.
On Wed, Oct 16, 2024 at 6:32â€¯PM Lucy Paredes <[lparedes@capitalareafoodbank.org

I have attached what I am able to see on my end as far as submitted reports. If you submitted them, you should have received an email with a PDF copy via email. If you could send me that, then it would clear up the missing inventory reports.

I did remember talking with you however I did not see your name on the sign in sheets, see attached document for reference. If you could please let me know which day you attended (I believe it was the last one) then I can send you the PDF copy for you to sign and return.
If you need any further clarification on either of the topics above, we can do a phone call tomorrow or Friday.
*{color:#172B4D} *From:*{color}* {color:#172B4D}New Hope And Life Church of God <{color}[{color:#172B4D}newhopeandlifechurchofgod@gmail.com{color}
*Subject:*  Re: Corrective Action Plan - New Hope and Life Church of God{color}

Good afternoon Lucy, I'm not sure I understand. These surveys were completed already. I signed the roster when I came into the training. Also, the certificate is at the Church. You and I spoke at the training when you told me about the corrective action. We will sign the corrective action plan and send it back next week.
On Wed, Oct 16, 2024 at 1:37â€¯PM Lucy Paredes <[lparedes@capitalareafoodbank.org
{color:#172B4D}Attached please find the corrective action plan for New Hope and Life Church of God. The following are the links for the monthly inventory reporting:{color}

{color:#172B4D}Dr. Head, could you please confirm your attendance for the civil rights training by sending the certificate received? Once received, I will forward you the sign-in sheet for you to sign and verify that you or a representative did indeed attend the training. If you did not attend, please let me know and I will send along the last 2 makeup dates.{color}

{color:#172B4D}I am here to help and support in any way that I can so please feel free to reach out to me via email as this is the best way to be able to refer back to information if there were ever any follow-up questions or concerns. I am also happy to touch base via phone call and I will always send a recap of the conversation via email.{color}
{color:#172B4D}Please return the signed corrective action plan, along with a summary of your plan for each issue outlined by Wednesday, October 23rd.{color}

thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""10/24/2024 01:31;712020:e3f1b9a5-afcd-4846-bd16-3cc8c3d8a80c;Dr. Head, 

  

We appreciate the wonderful service you provide to your community and your partnership with CAFB for the last 15 years. Different programs within CAFB have different rules and regulations. TEFAP falls under the rules and regulations of MD DHS, collection of SDI forms is one of the requirements set forth by them not by myself or by CAFB. 

  

I completely understand that the work that you and all your volunteers do is hard and exhausting work. We also understand that not everyone is able to, qualifies for, or feels comfortable completing the SDI form. This is why we do always recommend there be non TEFAP food set aside for those do not qualify or are unable to complete the SDI form. 

  

My goal is not to suspend New Hope and Life Church of God, it is to work with you and each partner to ensure there is compliance with regulations set forth by MD DHS, to work together when other problems arise, and to get to know each partner to the best of my ability so that I can continue to advocate for change at the state level. 

  

Regarding the monthly inventory report for the month of August, like covered in the civil rights training, regardless of whether food was distributed a report must still be submitted. In the case of no distribution, you would just need to put 0 under the household and individuals served, note any inventory you have at the time, sign and submit. 

I can also look at your sales order record and send you the food ordered around that time frame which may help in the completion of the report. 

  

I do want to remind you that I am out of town tomorrow Friday October 24th and Monday, October 28th. Like stated in the previous emails, what needs to be submitted on Wednesday, October 23rd is the signed corrective action plan, a summary of how you will be collecting SDI forms, and submission of the monthly inventory reports that have not yet been submitted. Submission of the reports can be through the links originally sent or if your organization completed the reports previously, they should have been sent an email copy of the report which can then be emailed to me. 

  

I appreciate your patience, understanding and the work you and you organization does for the community. 

  

Best, 

Lucy

{color:#172B4D} This is my second follow up with reference to acquiring access to my shopping account. Would someone be able to assist here?{color}

column1: Re: Memorial Day 5/27 ,PART1-6555,56497,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,B@yMgeRATrNBGrneOl.Co,TlNyen.BRBroGA@MCreOg,2024-05-13 04:31:00,2024-05-18 01:31:00,,2024-05-14 10:46:00,,"Hello thereâ€¦we can do delivery Tuesday May 28th if thatâ€™s okâ€¦

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused.

Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule.

In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding.
Thank you for your patience and cooperation.
{color:#4E8227}Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution{color}{color:#4E8227}{color}
{color:#3A7C22}4900 Puerto Rico Ave, NE Washington DC 20017{color}{color:#4E8227}{color}
{color:red}Please email all customer service questions or concerns to{color} [{color:red} {color}{color:red} *partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org*{color}{color:red} {color}
column2: mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org]{color:red} so that one of my colleagues or I can assist you promptly. Thank you!{color}{color:red}{color}{color:red}{color}

Thank you for reaching out. We will not be hosting another training session, but there are tools available to assist you. You can find a guide in PDF format called ""Hours of Operations"" under the Partner Resource Tab on PartnerLink. This document provides instructions on how to update your hours of operation. 

Once you are logged into PartnerLink, click on your agency name to access your Account Overview. Under Additional Information, you will find a button labeled ""Hours of Operations."" Click on it to view the hours currently listed for your agency. If the hours are correct, click ""verify"" to confirm. thumbnail!"", ""comment2"": ""11/20/2024 04:17;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,  

Thank you for reaching out to us. I am happy to provide you with access to all the sites, but I want to highlight a few important points.   

For individuals with access to multiple shopping accounts, please keep the following rules in mind: 

 1. You must use the logins provided below. Our system does not allow for a single account to access all your sites; each site requires a different set of credentials.     2. You cannot change the passwords listed below.   

3. You will not be able to use the ""forgot password"" tool. If you experience any issues with your login, please contact us at partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org. Because you are using the same email for logging in, clicking the ""forgot password"" option will affect all your other logins.  

Here are your credentials:  -

**NHT R. Street**     

Username: rjohnson@nhtinc.org     

Password: cafbshoppernht01  -

**NHT Monsenor Romero**     

Username: rjohnson@nhtinc.org     

Password: cafbshoppernht02  

**NHT Villages of East of the River**     

Username: rjohnson@nhtinc.org     

Password: cafbshoppernht03  

**NHT Washington View Apartments**     

Username: rjohnson@nhtinc.org     

Password: cafbshoppernht05  

Please note that we had temporary accounts for Galen Terrace and Mass Plass Apartments that were only active during COVID and have since been terminated. If you are interested in creating new accounts for these sites, please contact Laura Jeske at +12025409766 or [ljeske@capitalareafoodbank.org

Charity"", ""comment3"": ""01/24/2025 03:51;712020:b15fa988-bc60-49b4-aa6f-e30b7a3629c1;Hello,

Thank you for contacting customer support. Due to a recent update of our website, some partners may be experiencing issues with editing orders, or adding items to their cart. We are asking that if partnerâ€™s are experiencing any issues to please do a hard reset of your browser. Please clear the â€œcacheâ€ on the browser you are using and refresh the page to begin shopping again. You can either search online how to clear the cache for the specific browser you are using, or you can tell us which browser you are using and we will be happy to send you the instructions.

Please note that this is necessary as the settings on our website have changed and if the cache is not clear, it will function based off of the old settings.

Hope this helps,

Charity ""}",,0.0

column1: A few months ago, we were contacted about switching our distribution day from Tuesday to a later day in the week, and we agreed to move it to Wednesday. However, weâ€™ve found that having only one day between our distribution dates has been challenging for our volunteers and has created scheduling conflicts with some of our other pickups.

Now that the holidays are over, weâ€™d like to request switching back to our original Tuesday distribution. This change would allow us to serve the community more effectively and provide our volunteers with adequate time to recover between distributions.

We understand the importance of aligning with your delivery schedule and want to remain considerate of your operations. However, we would greatly appreciate it if this adjustment could be made. Please let us know if this is possible.
Looking forward to hearing from you.

I hope this message finds you well. Thank you for bringing this to our attention! I have discussed this matter with our leadership and the team involved in this initiative. We appreciate you reopening the discussion.

When we initiated this plan, our goal was to alleviate the burden on our Tuesday schedule due to the number of large deliveries we have on that day. However, we acknowledge the challenges this has caused for your agency, which was not our intended outcome. Letâ€™s work together to find a solution!

One option I wanted to explore with you is whether you would be open to either receiving all your food items on Fridays or accepting deliveries on Mondays instead of Tuesdays. Please let me know your preference, and if neither option works for you, I will take that information back to our department leaders and Operations for further consideration. Our aim is to ensure that we do not burden your distribution or volunteers.

Thank you, Pastor Oliver!

Best regards,

Re: Memorial Day 5/27 ,PART1-6559,56504,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,DH,ial@l.mgnoustoatcicoremmih,gmo.iamimhttr@lislocoeaunc,2024-05-13 05:24:00,2024-05-18 01:31:00,,2024-05-14 11:47:00,,"Hello we can take our delivery on 5/28 instead of 5/27
On Mon, May 13, 2024 at 4:10â€¯PM Partner Support <[partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org

We hope this message finds you well. We are reaching out to you today because we have discovered a system error that mistakenly marked Tuesday, May 28th as Memorial Day instead of Monday, May 27th. As a result, some of you were able to place an order for that day. We apologize for any confusion this may have caused.

Please be advised that on the actual day of Memorial Day - Monday, May 27th - Capital Area Food Bank will be closed. Because of this, we will need to move the day of your delivery to ensure that you receive your order on a different day that works with your schedule.

In order to make this change as quickly as possible, please respond to this message at your earliest convenience with the most convenient day for your delivery. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding.
Thank you for your patience and cooperation.
{color:#4e8227}Manager of Customer Relations & Distribution Network Evolution{color}{color:#4e8227}{color}
[{color:#3a7c22}4900 Puerto Rico Ave, NE Washington DC 20017{color}

M.,Request of Customer Relations,,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Agency Administration -> Connection to CAFB Staff,Email Request,English,Order Updated,0.0,,Email to Jira,7560,02:37:00,service-request,Done,2024-12-13 03:59:00,00:10:48.100000,"{""comment1"": ""12/13/2024 09:10;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning,

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. You can pick up donation boxes at the food bank from Monday to Friday, 8 AM to 4 PM, at our warehouse in Washington, DC. If you arrive between 8 AM and 2 PM, please go to the side of the warehouse designated for partner pickups. If you cannot come during those hours, please visit the front of the building where our receptionist is located, and ask for donation boxes from 2 PM to 4 PM.

Please note that our CAFB donation boxes cannot be used for partner donations. For example, you should not place them outside stores for accepting donations to your organization. If you are raising awareness and fundraising for your organization, please refrain from using the CAFB branded boxes.

Thank you,

column1: Order SO163215 ,PART1-6773,59607,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,CH,ifeRCihr s,hCf Riresi,2024-06-13 05:54:00,2024-06-20 01:30:00,,2024-06-14 01:09:00,,"Hi -
We received 1 - 825068 Cantaloupe FULL PALLET 72cs today. Sadly, we have gone through 40+ of the 72 cases (and going through more)
and the cantaloupe is moldy, and spoiled. We are disappointed that we are not able to give to our clients and this was a very bountiful item. Attached are some images showing the issue.

As we know we are not able to give out, we are asking and seeing if a truck can come to pick up to dispose. Having nearly 2600 pounds of spoiled food will dramatically take out our resources for disposing.
Thank you in advance for your quick response to this matter.

column2: mailto:partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org] because theyâ€™re more clued into warehouse closures than I am and should be able to answer your questions thoroughly.

column1: I am currently looking into Coastal produce box delivery capacity during holidays / the limit of the funding we have for those.
Looking at the end of 2024 and wanted to check on delivery dates for planning purposes.
*  Thanksgiving is Thursday, November 28th -- Will you have deliveries on Wednesday, November 27th?
*  Christmas is Wednesday, December 25th -- Will you have deliveries on Tuesday, December 24th?
*  New Year's Day is Wednesday, January 1st -- Will you have deliveries either Tuesday, Wednesday, or Thursday of that week?

* Image ""CAFB NB What Is This? B"" we have 20 cases and think it might be mustards, but kinda looks like kale.

Please advise on if we will receive the 4th pallet today.

CiArra "", ""comment2"": ""10/04/2024 02:23;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:982e2500-2736-4192-96ad-189e7c78cf11;Thank you, CiArra.

Judy"", ""comment3"": ""10/07/2024 01:13;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:982e2500-2736-4192-96ad-189e7c78cf11;Good afternoon, CiArra.

I hope you are doing well.

Do you have an update on the missing pallet? I am wondering whether to try to order the same items for this Fridayâ€™s delivery.

Thanks,

Judy"", ""comment4"": ""10/09/2024 06:00;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon Judy,

I hope this message finds you well. I have been working with CiArra to resolve this issue, and unfortunately, we were not able to locate your missing items in the warehouse. We sincerely apologize for this inconvenience and are taking steps to ensure it does not happen again. I have processed a credit for your agency, which will be applied to the invoice related to this order (Invoice 178408, Credit is: 8236). The credit amount for the missing items is $595.95. We are actively working to improve our delivery and fulfillment processes and appreciate your understanding and patience during this time. I have already escalated this issue to our leadership and informed them of the impact it has had on your distributions. 

If you need anything from us, please let us know. Once again, we apologize for this inconvenience.

I appreciate your help.

Judy"", ""comment6"": ""10/09/2024 06:17;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;Customer has replied after the ticket has been resolved.""}",,0.0

Judy",NW C. F.,Request of Customer Relations,800107 Winter squash,DC,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Menu -> General Questions,Questions about Shopping Menu Items,English,Explanation Provided,4.0,2024-11-07 11:03:00,Email to Jira,7200,,service-request,Done,2024-11-07 10:59:00,00:34:06.800000,"{""comment1"": ""11/07/2024 10:34;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good afternoon,

Thank you for reaching out to Customer Service. After speaking with our Head of Procurement, he clarified that there can sometimes be a mix of winter squash, but he believes this one is butternut squash.

Thank you,  
""D"""", ""comment2"": ""11/07/2024 10:38;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:982e2500-2736-4192-96ad-189e7c78cf11;Thank you, ""D"".

I did end up deleting this one from our shopping cart because the butternut squash is too big for many of our guests and our volunteers to handle. If there is any way to provide more detail about the produce offerings it would be really helpful.

Judy"", ""comment3"": ""11/07/2024 10:58;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Hi Judy! Yes, we are collaborating with our internal teams to provide additional details about the items when they arrive at the food bank, and we are also ensuring that there are photos included. For some of our produce, the descriptions can be broader, and when items are received, they may be mixed. For example, we might receive potatoes, but three bins could contain one type, while the other four contain a different type, and they are all categorized simply as potatoes. We are definitely working on improving descriptions to enhance the overall experience. 

Best,  
""D""""}",,0.0

{color:#715FFA}On Friday, September 13, 2024, 3:35 PM, Customer Support (partnersupport@capitalareafoodbank.org) <system@sent-via.netsuite.com> wrote:{color}

If you are receiving this email, it means you have not yet attended one of our mandatory Hours of Operations Trainings. There is a new feature available on PartnerLink that allows partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This feature will enable you to keep your records up to date as required, which is important for ensuring that we have the most current information in our internal systems for our clients to use.
Once approved, the information collected from your updates will be linked to our online tool that clients can use to find food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to use this function, we have hosted three trainings, and there is one session remaining on  {color:#e03e2d}*September 19th from 9 am to 10 am*{color}{color:#e03e2d}.{color} These sessions have been designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and provide an opportunity to speak to our team about PartnerLink and offer feedback. Please note that this training is mandatory. You can use this link to [register

Once you fill out the form entirely, a Zoom link with a calendar invite will be sent to your email. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We suggest that this person work closely with the food program and have a deep understanding of operations.

Our Lady of Perpetual Help Church{color:#575757}{color}"", ""comment9"": ""08/16/2024 01:49;712020:b15fa988-bc60-49b4-aa6f-e30b7a3629c1;Good afternoon,
Â 
We contacted the TEFAP Team and learned that we anticipate receiving a shipment of catfish between October 16th and 31st. Currently, we do not have a waitlist or a reminder system linked to our inventory to alert partners when items are back in stock. This is feedback we have received from partners and have conveyed to our Food Resourcing and Inventory Teams for consideration.
Â 
If you wish to check back during that time and do not see the catfish available, we would be happy to reach out to the TEFAP team to confirm if the shipment is still expected during that period. It seems that in your original order, the product went out of stock. Our inventory is live and operates on a first-come, first-served basis as you know. At times, items may be taken by the time you start the checkout process, resulting in an error message prompting you to update your item quantities based on what's available.
Â 
Additionally, there may be different lots of items with varying expiration dates. Consequently, you may have two lots of the same product arriving at different times, with one having a later expiration date than the other. Depending on the date of your order, the item may have gone out of stock for the specific case lot you selected, even though there are still some available on the menu. This occurs due to the date you chose for your order.
Â 
We acknowledge that our inventory system is complex and are striving to make it more user-friendly and accessible for partners to obtain information from the website.
Â 
Thank you,
Customer Relations""}",,0.0

Re: New PartnerLink Feature- only 2 more training sessions left! ,PART1-7320,67375,[System] Service request,Closed,PART1,Partner Support,Medium,Done,CH,oesy.msns.eneittetiscm-at@uv,mo.nese-teicttinemvt@.sussya,2024-09-03 11:12:00,2024-09-07 01:32:00,,2024-09-03 12:08:00,,"{color:#172B4D}Good morning CAFB,{color}
{color:#172B4D} We, at PEAN foodbank registered for the mandatory training for today. No link received yet. #3016484884. Please advise if there is no training for today.{color}
*Subject:* New PartnerLink Feature- only 2 more training sessions left!{color}

We are excited to announce that the new PartnerLink feature is now live! This feature will allow partners to update their hours of operations for their distributions. This new feature is very exciting because it means that you will be able to update your records whenever necessary. This ensures that we have the most up-to-date information in our internal systems and for clients to utilize. As a reminder, once approved, the information we gather from your updates will be linked to the information provided in our online tool that clients can use to locate food assistance: [Get Help Map

To ensure that all partners understand how to utilize this function, we planned to host two trainings, two of which have already occurred and  *+two+* more in the month of September. These sessions are designed to demonstrate how to use this feature and also provide an opportunity to talk to our team about PartnerLink and provide feedback. Please note that this training is  *+mandatory+*. You can use the links below to register your agency. We only require one representative per agency to attend, but we welcome and encourage all shoppers who have access to PartnerLink to join. We recommend that this person work closely with the food program and has a deep understanding of operations. While the training will be recorded and slides will be shared,  *all partners are expected to attend the live training to fulfill the requirement*. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Customer Relations.

column2: https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=4eNCVd-_qki8SMWEhD1eIsYv8jPOqcdPqqy5Ip3OhsZUN1ZKWjFLWk5EV1NHOUFSSjFLUUtaQ1E3OS4u] to register. Upon selecting a training date and completing the form, you will receive the corresponding Zoom link via email.

column1: We are also excited to announce that the Customer Relations team will be hosting office hours every Wednesday in August & September from 10 am to 11 am starting August 14th. If you have any questions or support needs related to the new PartnerLink feature, this time is available to you.

Additionally, this opportunity will allow partners to interact with the Customer Relations Team, ask questions, and receive additional support regarding PartnerLink, menu items, new website features, and more. Please come prepared with questions and examples of issues that you may be experiencing with PartnerLink. Sharing your experiences is valuable, as it could help others facing similar issues. If you have specific recurring issues unique to your organization, we may need to take down your information and set up a one-on-one meeting to address them thoroughly and ensure the office hours are productive for all partners. Please note that if there are no attendees in the first 15 minutes of the office hours, we will cancel that week's session.
To register for Customer Relations office hours, please click [here
We appreciate your ongoing partnership, collaboration, and look forward to seeing you at one of our training sessions or during our office hours.

C.,Request of Customer Relations,,MD,Partner Support / Customer Support,,Orders - Pre delivery -> General Questions,Pickup & Delivery Support,English,Question Answered,0.0,,Portal,,,service-request,Done,2025-01-02 12:12:00,00:11:50.900000,"{""comment1"": ""01/02/2025 12:11;61536ea272f6970069fc1dbd;Good morning!

I hope you are doing well. Happy New Year! Since we were closed from December 25th until January 2nd, the last day to place an order for January 6th was December 24th, in accordance with our three business day fulfillment rule. This is why you were unable to make an order for January 6th, and we sincerely apologize for any inconvenience.

Please note that anytime a day is marked in gray on the calendar, it either means that the calendar is full or the day is no longer available due to the deadline for placing an order having passed.

You can schedule a delivery or pickup for Tuesday, January 7th, until the end of the day on January 3rd. There are still some slots available, so please take a look soon to secure an available time.

Thank you,

""D""""}",,0.0
